120 static void expandCompound(const TopoShape& shape, std::vector<TopoShape>& res)
121 {
122  if (shape.isNull()) {
123  FC_THROWM(NullShapeException, "Null input shape");
124  }
125  if (shape.getShape().ShapeType() != TopAbs_COMPOUND) {
126  res.push_back(shape);
127  return;
128  }
129  for (auto& s : shape.getSubTopoShapes()) {
130  expandCompound(s, res);
131  }
132 }

134 void TopoShape::initCache(int reset) const
135 {
136  if (reset > 0 || !_cache || _cache->isTouched(_Shape)) {
137  if (_parentCache) {
138  _parentCache.reset();
139  _subLocation.Identity();
140  }
141  _cache = std::make_shared<TopoShapeCache>(_Shape);
142  }
143 }
144 
145 Data::ElementMapPtr TopoShape::resetElementMap(Data::ElementMapPtr elementMap)
146 {
147  if (_cache && elementMap != this->elementMap(false)) {
148  for (auto& info : _cache->shapeAncestryCache) {
149  info.clear();
150  }
151  }
152  else {
153  initCache();
154  }
155  if (elementMap) {
156  _cache->cachedElementMap = elementMap;
157  _cache->subLocation.Identity();
158  _subLocation.Identity();
159  _parentCache.reset();
160  }
161  return Data::ComplexGeoData::resetElementMap(elementMap);
162 }
163 
164 void TopoShape::flushElementMap() const
165 {
166  initCache();
167  if (!elementMap(false) && this->_cache) {
168  if (this->_cache->cachedElementMap) {
169  const_cast<TopoShape*>(this)->resetElementMap(this->_cache->cachedElementMap);
170  }
171  else if (this->_parentCache) {
172  TopoShape parent(this->Tag, this->Hasher, this->_parentCache->shape);
173  parent._cache = _parentCache;
174  parent.flushElementMap();
175  TopoShape self(this->Tag,
176  this->Hasher,
177  this->_Shape.Located(this->_subLocation * this->_cache->subLocation));
178  self._cache = _cache;
179  self.mapSubElement(parent);
180  this->_parentCache.reset();
181  this->_subLocation.Identity();
182  const_cast<TopoShape*>(this)->resetElementMap(self.elementMap());
183  }
184  }
185 }
186 
187 void TopoShape::setShape(const TopoDS_Shape& shape, bool resetElementMap)
188 {
189  if (resetElementMap) {
190  this->resetElementMap();
191  }
192  else if (_cache && _cache->isTouched(shape)) {
193  this->flushElementMap();
194  }
195  //_Shape._Shape = shape; // TODO: Replace the next line with this once ShapeProtector is
196  // available.
197  _Shape = shape;
198  if (_cache) {
199  initCache();
200  }
201 }

223 TopoDS_Shape& TopoShape::move(TopoDS_Shape& tds, const gp_Trsf& transfer)
224 {
225 #if OCC_VERSION_HEX < 0x070600
226  static constexpr double scalePrecision {1e-14};
227  if (std::abs(transfer.ScaleFactor()) > scalePrecision)
228 #else
229  if (std::abs(transfer.ScaleFactor()) > TopLoc_Location::ScalePrec())
230 #endif
231  {
232  auto transferCopy(transfer);
233  transferCopy.SetScaleFactor(1.0);
234  tds.Move(transferCopy);
235  }
236  else {
237  tds.Move(transfer);
238  }
239  return tds;
240 }

294 TopoDS_Shape TopoShape::findShape(const char* name) const
295 {
296  if (!name) {
297  return {};
298  }
299 
300  Data::MappedElement res = getElementName(name);
301  if (!res.index) {
302  return {};
303  }
304 
305  auto idx = shapeTypeAndIndex(name);
306  if (idx.second == 0) {
307  return {};
308  }
309  initCache();
310  return _cache->findShape(_Shape, idx.first, idx.second);
311 }

319 std::vector<TopoShape> TopoShape::findSubShapesWithSharedVertex(const TopoShape& subshape,
320  std::vector<std::string>* names,
321  Data::SearchOptions options,
322  double tol,
323  double atol) const
324 {
325  bool checkGeometry = options.testFlag(Data::SearchOption::CheckGeometry);
326  bool singleSearch = options.testFlag(Data::SearchOption::SingleResult);
327  std::vector<TopoShape> res;
328  if (subshape.isNull() || this->isNull()) {
329  return res;
330  }
331  double tol2 = tol * tol;
332  int index = 0;
333  TopAbs_ShapeEnum shapeType = subshape.shapeType();
334 
335  // This is an intentionally recursive method, which will exit after looking through all
336  // ancestors.
337  auto searchCompositeShape = [&](TopAbs_ShapeEnum childType) { // NOLINT (misc-no-recu2rsive)
338  unsigned long count = subshape.countSubShapes(childType);
339  if (!count) {
340  return;
341  }
342  auto first = subshape.getSubTopoShape(childType, 1);
343  for (const auto& child :
344  findSubShapesWithSharedVertex(first, nullptr, options, tol, atol)) {
345  for (int idx : findAncestors(child.getShape(), shapeType)) {
346  auto shape = getSubTopoShape(shapeType, idx);
347  if (shape.countSubShapes(childType) != count) {
348  continue;
349  }
350  bool found = true;
351  for (unsigned long i = 2; i < count; ++i) {
352  if (shape
353  .findSubShapesWithSharedVertex(subshape.getSubTopoShape(childType, i),
354  nullptr,
355  options,
356  tol,
357  atol)
358  .empty()) {
359  found = false;
360  break;
361  }
362  }
363  if (found) {
364  res.push_back(shape);
365  if (names) {
366  names->push_back(shapeName(shapeType) + std::to_string(idx));
367  }
368  if (singleSearch) {
369  return;
370  }
371  }
372  }
373  }
374  };
375 
376  switch (shapeType) {
377  case TopAbs_WIRE:
378  searchCompositeShape(TopAbs_EDGE);
379  break;
380  case TopAbs_SHELL:
381  searchCompositeShape(TopAbs_FACE);
382  break;
383  case TopAbs_SOLID:
384  searchCompositeShape(TopAbs_SHELL);
385  break;
386  case TopAbs_COMPSOLID:
387  searchCompositeShape(TopAbs_SOLID);
388  break;
389  case TopAbs_COMPOUND:
390  // special treatment of single sub-shape compound, that is, search
391  // its extracting the compound
392  if (countSubShapes(TopAbs_SHAPE) == 1) {
393  return findSubShapesWithSharedVertex(subshape.getSubTopoShape(TopAbs_SHAPE, 1),
394  names,
395  options,
396  tol,
397  atol);
398  }
399  else if (unsigned long count = countSubShapes(TopAbs_SHAPE)) {
400  // For multi-sub-shape compound, only search for compound with the same
401  // structure
402  int idx = 0;
403  for (const auto& compound : getSubTopoShapes(shapeType)) {
404  ++idx;
405  if (compound.countSubShapes(TopAbs_SHAPE) != count) {
406  continue;
407  }
408  int i = 0;
409  bool found = true;
410  for (const auto& s : compound.getSubTopoShapes(TopAbs_SHAPE)) {
411  ++i;
412  auto ss = subshape.getSubTopoShape(TopAbs_SHAPE, i);
413  if (ss.isNull() && s.isNull()) {
414  continue;
415  }
416  auto options2 = options;
417  options2.setFlag(Data::SearchOption::SingleResult);
418  if (ss.isNull() || s.isNull() || ss.shapeType() != s.shapeType()
419  || ss.findSubShapesWithSharedVertex(s, nullptr, options2, tol, atol)
420  .empty()) {
421  found = false;
422  break;
423  }
424  }
425  if (found) {
426  if (names) {
427  names->push_back(shapeName(shapeType) + std::to_string(idx));
428  }
429  res.push_back(compound);
430  if (singleSearch) {
431  return res;
432  }
433  }
434  }
435  }
436  break;
437  case TopAbs_VERTEX:
438  // Vertex search will do comparison with tolerance to account for
439  // rounding error inccured through transformation.
440  for (auto& shape : getSubTopoShapes(TopAbs_VERTEX)) {
441  ++index;
442  if (BRep_Tool::Pnt(TopoDS::Vertex(shape.getShape()))
443  .SquareDistance(BRep_Tool::Pnt(TopoDS::Vertex(subshape.getShape())))
444  <= tol2) {
445  if (names) {
446  names->push_back(std::string("Vertex") + std::to_string(index));
447  }
448  res.push_back(shape);
449  if (singleSearch) {
450  return res;
451  }
452  }
453  }
454  break;
455  case TopAbs_EDGE:
456  case TopAbs_FACE: {
457  std::unique_ptr<Geometry> geom;
458  bool isLine = false;
459  bool isPlane = false;
460 
461  std::vector<TopoDS_Shape> vertices;
462  TopoShape wire;
463  if (shapeType == TopAbs_FACE) {
464  wire = subshape.splitWires();
465  vertices = wire.getSubShapes(TopAbs_VERTEX);
466  }
467  else {
468  vertices = subshape.getSubShapes(TopAbs_VERTEX);
469  }
470 
471  if (vertices.empty() || checkGeometry) {
472  geom = Geometry::fromShape(subshape.getShape(), true);
473  if (!geom) {
474  return res;
475  }
476  if (shapeType == TopAbs_EDGE) {
477  isLine = (geom->isDerivedFrom(GeomLine::getClassTypeId())
478  || geom->isDerivedFrom(GeomLineSegment::getClassTypeId()));
479  }
480  else {
481  isPlane = geom->isDerivedFrom(GeomPlane::getClassTypeId());
482  }
483  }
484 
485  auto compareGeometry = [&](const TopoShape& s, bool strict) {
486  std::unique_ptr<Geometry> g2(Geometry::fromShape(s.getShape(), true));
487  if (!g2) {
488  return false;
489  }
490  if (isLine && !strict) {
491  // For lines, don't compare geometry, just check the
492  // vertices below instead, because the exact same edge
493  // may have different geometrical representation.
494  if (!g2->isDerivedFrom(GeomLine::getClassTypeId())
495  && !g2->isDerivedFrom(GeomLineSegment::getClassTypeId())) {
496  return false;
497  }
498  }
499  else if (isPlane && !strict) {
500  // For planes, don't compare geometry either, so that
501  // we don't need to worry about orientation and so on.
502  // Just check the edges.
503  if (!g2->isDerivedFrom(GeomPlane::getClassTypeId())) {
504  return false;
505  }
506  }
507  else if (!g2 || !g2->isSame(*geom, tol, atol)) {
508  return false;
509  }
510  return true;
511  };
512 
513  if (vertices.empty()) {
514  // Probably an infinite shape, so we have to search by geometry
515  int idx = 0;
516  for (auto& shape : getSubTopoShapes(shapeType)) {
517  ++idx;
518  if (!shape.countSubShapes(TopAbs_VERTEX) && compareGeometry(shape, true)) {
519  if (names) {
520  names->push_back(shapeName(shapeType) + std::to_string(idx));
521  }
522  res.push_back(shape);
523  if (singleSearch) {
524  return res;
525  }
526  }
527  }
528  break;
529  }
530 
531  // The basic idea of shape search is about the same for both edge and face.
532  // * Search the first vertex, which is done with tolerance.
533  // * Find the ancestor shape of the found vertex
534  // * Compare each vertex of the ancestor shape and the input shape
535  // * Perform geometry comparison of the ancestor and input shape.
536  // * For face, perform addition geometry comparison of each edge.
537  std::unordered_set<TopoShape, ShapeHasher, ShapeHasher> shapeSet;
538  for (auto& vert :
539  findSubShapesWithSharedVertex(vertices[0], nullptr, options, tol, atol)) {
540  for (auto idx : findAncestors(vert.getShape(), shapeType)) {
541  auto shape = getSubTopoShape(shapeType, idx);
542  if (!shapeSet.insert(shape).second) {
543  continue;
544  }
545  TopoShape otherWire;
546  std::vector<TopoDS_Shape> otherVertices;
547  if (shapeType == TopAbs_FACE) {
548  otherWire = shape.splitWires();
549  if (wire.countSubShapes(TopAbs_EDGE)
550  != otherWire.countSubShapes(TopAbs_EDGE)) {
551  continue;
552  }
553  otherVertices = otherWire.getSubShapes(TopAbs_VERTEX);
554  }
555  else {
556  otherVertices = shape.getSubShapes(TopAbs_VERTEX);
557  }
558  if (otherVertices.size() != vertices.size()) {
559  continue;
560  }
561  if (checkGeometry && !compareGeometry(shape, false)) {
562  continue;
563  }
564  unsigned ind = 0;
565  bool matched = true;
566  for (auto& vertex : vertices) {
567  bool found = false;
568  for (unsigned inner = 0; inner < otherVertices.size(); ++inner) {
569  auto& vertex1 = otherVertices[ind];
570  if (++ind == otherVertices.size()) {
571  ind = 0;
572  }
573  if (BRep_Tool::Pnt(TopoDS::Vertex(vertex))
574  .SquareDistance(BRep_Tool::Pnt(TopoDS::Vertex(vertex1)))
575  <= tol2) {
576  found = true;
577  break;
578  }
579  }
580  if (!found) {
581  matched = false;
582  break;
583  }
584  }
585  if (!matched) {
586  continue;
587  }
588 
589  if (shapeType == TopAbs_FACE && checkGeometry) {
590  // Is it really necessary to check geometries of each edge of a face?
591  // Right now we only do outer wire check
592  auto otherEdges = otherWire.getSubShapes(TopAbs_EDGE);
593  std::vector<std::unique_ptr<Geometry>> geos;
594  geos.resize(otherEdges.size());
595  bool matched2 = true;
596  unsigned i = 0;
597  auto edges = wire.getSubShapes(TopAbs_EDGE);
598  for (auto& edge : edges) {
599  std::unique_ptr<Geometry> geom2(Geometry::fromShape(edge, true));
600  if (!geom2) {
601  matched2 = false;
602  break;
603  }
604  bool isLine2 = false;
605  gp_Pnt pt1, pt2;
606  if (geom2->isDerivedFrom(GeomLine::getClassTypeId())
607  || geom2->isDerivedFrom(GeomLineSegment::getClassTypeId())) {
608  pt1 = BRep_Tool::Pnt(TopExp::FirstVertex(TopoDS::Edge(edge)));
609  pt2 = BRep_Tool::Pnt(TopExp::LastVertex(TopoDS::Edge(edge)));
610  isLine2 = true;
611  }
612  // We will tolerate on edge reordering
613  bool found = false;
614  for (unsigned j = 0; j < otherEdges.size(); j++) {
615  auto& e1 = otherEdges[i];
616  auto& g1 = geos[i];
617  if (++i >= otherEdges.size()) {
618  i = 0;
619  }
620  if (!g1) {
621  g1 = Geometry::fromShape(e1, true);
622  if (!g1) {
623  break;
624  }
625  }
626  if (isLine2) {
627  if (g1->isDerivedFrom(GeomLine::getClassTypeId())
628  || g1->isDerivedFrom(GeomLineSegment::getClassTypeId())) {
629  auto p1 =
630  BRep_Tool::Pnt(TopExp::FirstVertex(TopoDS::Edge(e1)));
631  auto p2 =
632  BRep_Tool::Pnt(TopExp::LastVertex(TopoDS::Edge(e1)));
633  if ((p1.SquareDistance(pt1) <= tol2
634  && p2.SquareDistance(pt2) <= tol2)
635  || (p1.SquareDistance(pt2) <= tol2
636  && p2.SquareDistance(pt1) <= tol2)) {
637  found = true;
638  break;
639  }
640  }
641  continue;
642  }
643 
644  if (g1->isSame(*geom2, tol, atol)) {
645  found = true;
646  break;
647  }
648  }
649  if (!found) {
650  matched2 = false;
651  break;
652  }
653  }
654  if (!matched2) {
655  continue;
656  }
657  }
658  if (names) {
659  names->push_back(shapeName(shapeType) + std::to_string(idx));
660  }
661  res.push_back(shape);
662  }
663  }
664  break;
665  }
666  default:
667  break;
668  }
669  return res;
670 }

721 bool TopoShape::canMapElement(const TopoShape& other) const
722 {
723  if (isNull() || other.isNull() || this == &other || other.Tag == -1 || Tag == -1) {
724  return false;
725  }
726  if ((other.Tag == 0) && !other.elementMap(false) && !other.hasPendingElementMap()) {
727  return false;

732  return true;

740 {

775 void TopoShape::copyElementMap(const TopoShape& topoShape, const char* op)
776 {
777  if (topoShape.isNull() || isNull()) {
778  return;
779  }
780  std::vector<Data::ElementMap::MappedChildElements> children;
781  std::array<TopAbs_ShapeEnum, 3> elementTypes = {TopAbs_VERTEX, TopAbs_EDGE, TopAbs_FACE};
782  for (const auto elementType : elementTypes) {
783  auto count = checkSubshapeCount(*this, topoShape, elementType);
784  if (count == 0) {
785  continue;
786  }
787  children.emplace_back();
788  auto& child = children.back();
789  setupChild(child, elementType, topoShape, count, op);
790  }
791  resetElementMap();
792  if (!Hasher) {
793  Hasher = topoShape.Hasher;
794  }
795  setMappedChildElements(children);
796 }

799 // TODO: Refactor mapSubElementTypeForShape to reduce complexity
800 void TopoShape::mapSubElementTypeForShape(const TopoShape& other,
801  TopAbs_ShapeEnum type,
802  const char* op,
803  int count,
804  bool forward,
805  bool& warned)
806 {
807  auto& shapeMap = _cache->getAncestry(type);
808  auto& otherMap = other._cache->getAncestry(type);
809  const char* shapeType = shapeName(type).c_str();
810 
811  // 1-indexed for readability (e.g. there is no "Edge0", we started at "Edge1", etc.)
812  for (int outerCounter = 1; outerCounter <= count; ++outerCounter) {
813  int innerCounter {0};
814  int index {0};
815  if (forward) {
816  innerCounter = outerCounter;
817  index = shapeMap.find(_Shape, otherMap.find(other._Shape, outerCounter));
818  if (index == 0) {
819  continue;
820  }
821  }
822  else {
823  index = outerCounter;
824  innerCounter = otherMap.find(other._Shape, shapeMap.find(_Shape, outerCounter));
825  if (innerCounter == 0) {
826  continue;
827  }
828  }
829  Data::IndexedName element = Data::IndexedName::fromConst(shapeType, index);
830  for (auto& mappedName :
831  other.getElementMappedNames(Data::IndexedName::fromConst(shapeType, innerCounter),
832  true)) {
833  auto& name = mappedName.first;
834  auto& sids = mappedName.second;
835  if (!sids.empty()) {
836  if (!Hasher) {
837  Hasher = sids[0].getHasher();
838  }
839  else if (!sids[0].isFromSameHasher(Hasher)) {
840  if (!warned) {
841  warned = true;
842  FC_WARN("hasher mismatch"); // NOLINT
843  }
844  sids.clear();
845  }
846  }
847  char elementType {shapeName(type)[0]};
848 
849  std::ostringstream ss;
850  ensureElementMap()->encodeElementName(elementType, name, ss, &sids, Tag, op, other.Tag);
851  elementMap()->setElementName(element, name, Tag, &sids);
852  }
853  }
854 }

856 void TopoShape::mapSubElementForShape(const TopoShape& other, const char* op)
857 {
858  bool warned = false;
859  static const std::array<TopAbs_ShapeEnum, 3> types = {TopAbs_VERTEX, TopAbs_EDGE, TopAbs_FACE};
860 
861  for (auto type : types) {
862  auto& shapeMap = _cache->getAncestry(type);
863  auto& otherMap = other._cache->getAncestry(type);
864  if ((shapeMap.count() == 0) || (otherMap.count() == 0)) {
865  continue;
866  }
867 
868  bool forward {false};
869  int count {0};
870  if (otherMap.count() <= shapeMap.count()) {
871  forward = true;
872  count = otherMap.count();
873  }
874  else {
875  forward = false;
876  count = shapeMap.count();
877  }
878  mapSubElementTypeForShape(other, type, op, count, forward, warned);
879  }

882 void TopoShape::mapSubElement(const TopoShape& other, const char* op, bool forceHasher)
883 {
884  if (!canMapElement(other)) {
885  return;
886  }
887 
888  if (!getElementMapSize(false) && this->_Shape.IsPartner(other._Shape)) {
889  if (!this->Hasher) {
890  this->Hasher = other.Hasher;
891  }
892  copyElementMap(other, op);
893  return;
894  }
895 
896  bool warned = false;
897  static const std::array<TopAbs_ShapeEnum, 3> types = {TopAbs_VERTEX, TopAbs_EDGE, TopAbs_FACE};
898 
899  auto checkHasher = [this](const TopoShape& other) {
900  if (Hasher) {
901  if (other.Hasher != Hasher) {
902  if (!getElementMapSize(false)) {
903  if (FC_LOG_INSTANCE.isEnabled(FC_LOGLEVEL_LOG)) {
904  FC_WARN("hasher mismatch");
905  }
906  }
907  else {
908  // FC_THROWM(Base::RuntimeError, "hasher mismatch");
909  FC_ERR("hasher mismatch");
910  }
911  Hasher = other.Hasher;
912  }
913  }
914  else {
915  Hasher = other.Hasher;
916  }
917  };
918 
919  for (auto type : types) {
920  auto& shapeMap = _cache->getAncestry(type);
921  auto& otherMap = other._cache->getAncestry(type);
922  if (!shapeMap.count() || !otherMap.count()) {
923  continue;
924  }
925  if (!forceHasher && other.Hasher) {
926  forceHasher = true;
927  checkHasher(other);
928  }
929  const char* shapetype = shapeName(type).c_str();
930  std::ostringstream ss;
931 
932  bool forward;
933  int count;
934  if (otherMap.count() <= shapeMap.count()) {
935  forward = true;
936  count = otherMap.count();
937  }
938  else {
939  forward = false;
940  count = shapeMap.count();
941  }
942  for (int k = 1; k <= count; ++k) {
943  int i, idx;
944  if (forward) {
945  i = k;
946  idx = shapeMap.find(_Shape, otherMap.find(other._Shape, k));
947  if (!idx) {
948  continue;
949  }
950  }
951  else {
952  idx = k;
953  i = otherMap.find(other._Shape, shapeMap.find(_Shape, k));
954  if (!i) {
955  continue;
956  }
957  }
958  Data::IndexedName element = Data::IndexedName::fromConst(shapetype, idx);
959  for (auto& v :
960  other.getElementMappedNames(Data::IndexedName::fromConst(shapetype, i), true)) {
961  auto& name = v.first;
962  auto& sids = v.second;
963  if (sids.size()) {
964  if (!Hasher) {
965  Hasher = sids[0].getHasher();
966  }
967  else if (!sids[0].isFromSameHasher(Hasher)) {
968  if (!warned) {
969  warned = true;
970  FC_WARN("hasher mismatch");
971  }
972  sids.clear();
973  }
974  }
975  ss.str("");
976 
977  ensureElementMap()->encodeElementName(shapetype[0], name, ss, &sids, Tag, op, other.Tag);
978  elementMap()->setElementName(element, name, Tag, &sids);
979  }
980  }
981  }
982 }

991 std::vector<Data::ElementMap::MappedChildElements>
992 TopoShape::createChildMap(size_t count, const std::vector<TopoShape>& shapes, const char* op)
993 {
994  std::vector<Data::ElementMap::MappedChildElements> children;
995  children.reserve(count * (size_t)3);
996  std::array<TopAbs_ShapeEnum, 3> types = {TopAbs_VERTEX, TopAbs_EDGE, TopAbs_FACE};
997  for (const auto topAbsType : types) {
998  size_t offset = 0;
999  for (auto& topoShape : shapes) {
1000  if (topoShape.isNull()) {
1001  continue;
1002  }
1003  auto subShapeCount = topoShape.countSubShapes(topAbsType);
1004  if (subShapeCount == 0) {
1005  continue;
1006  }
1007  children.emplace_back();
1008  auto& child = children.back();
1009  child.indexedName =
1010  Data::IndexedName::fromConst(TopoShape::shapeName(topAbsType).c_str(), 1);
1011  child.offset = static_cast<int>(offset);
1012  offset += subShapeCount;
1013  child.count = static_cast<int>(subShapeCount);
1014  child.elementMap = topoShape.elementMap();
1015  child.tag = topoShape.Tag;
1016  if (op) {
1017  child.postfix = op;
1018  }
1019  }
1020  }
1021  return children;
1022 }

1024 void TopoShape::mapCompoundSubElements(const std::vector<TopoShape>& shapes, const char* op)
1025 {
1026  int count = 0;
1027  for (auto& topoShape : shapes) {
1028  if (topoShape.isNull()) {
1029  continue;
1030  }
1031  ++count;
1032  auto subshape = getSubShape(TopAbs_SHAPE, count, /*silent = */ true);
1033  if (!subshape.IsPartner(topoShape._Shape)) {
1034  return; // Not a partner shape, don't do any mapping at all
1035  }
1036  }
1037  auto children {createChildMap(count, shapes, op)};
1038  setMappedChildElements(children);

1041 void TopoShape::mapSubElement(const std::vector<TopoShape>& shapes, const char* op)
1042 {
1043  if (shapes.empty()) {
1044  return;
1045  }
1046 
1047  if (shapeType(true) == TopAbs_COMPOUND) {
1048  int count = 0;
1049  for (auto& s : shapes) {
1050  if (s.isNull()) {
1051  continue;
1052  }
1053  if (!getSubShape(TopAbs_SHAPE, ++count, true).IsPartner(s._Shape)) {
1054  count = 0;
1055  break;
1056  }
1057  }
1058  if (count) {
1059  std::vector<Data::ElementMap::MappedChildElements> children;
1060  children.reserve(count * 3);
1061  TopAbs_ShapeEnum types[] = {TopAbs_VERTEX, TopAbs_EDGE, TopAbs_FACE};
1062  for (unsigned i = 0; i < sizeof(types) / sizeof(types[0]); ++i) {
1063  int offset = 0;
1064  for (auto& s : shapes) {
1065  if (s.isNull()) {
1066  continue;
1067  }
1068  int count = s.countSubShapes(types[i]);
1069  if (!count) {
1070  continue;
1071  }
1072  children.emplace_back();
1073  auto& child = children.back();
1074  child.indexedName =
1075  Data::IndexedName::fromConst(shapeName(types[i]).c_str(), 1);
1076  child.offset = offset;
1077  offset += count;
1078  child.count = count;
1079  child.elementMap = s.elementMap();
1080  child.tag = s.Tag;
1081  if (op) {
1082  child.postfix = op;
1083  }
1084  }
1085  }
1086  setMappedChildElements(children);
1087  return;
1088  }
1089  }
1090 
1091  for (auto& shape : shapes) {
1092  mapSubElement(shape, op);
1093  }
1094 }

1096 std::vector<TopoDS_Shape> TopoShape::getSubShapes(TopAbs_ShapeEnum type,
1097  TopAbs_ShapeEnum avoid) const
1098 {
1099  std::vector<TopoDS_Shape> ret;
1100  if (isNull()) {
1101  return ret;
1102  }
1103  if (avoid != TopAbs_SHAPE) {
1104  for (TopExp_Explorer exp(getShape(), type, avoid); exp.More(); exp.Next()) {
1105  ret.push_back(exp.Current());
1106  }
1107  return ret;
1108  }
1109  initCache();
1110  auto& ancestry = _cache->getAncestry(type);
1111  int count = ancestry.count();
1112  ret.reserve(count);
1113  for (int i = 1; i <= count; ++i) {
1114  ret.push_back(ancestry.find(_Shape, i));
1115  }
1116  return ret;
1117 }

1141 std::vector<TopoShape> TopoShape::getOrderedEdges(MapElement mapElement) const
1142 {
1143  if (isNull()) {
1144  return std::vector<TopoShape>();
1145  }
1146 
1147  std::vector<TopoShape> shapes;
1148  if (shapeType() == TopAbs_WIRE) {
1149  BRepTools_WireExplorer xp(TopoDS::Wire(getShape()));
1150  while (xp.More()) {
1151  shapes.push_back(TopoShape(xp.Current()));
1152  xp.Next();
1153  }
1154  }
1155  else {
1156  // INIT_SHAPE_CACHE();
1157  initCache();
1158  for (const auto& w : getSubShapes(TopAbs_WIRE)) {
1159  BRepTools_WireExplorer xp(TopoDS::Wire(w));
1160  while (xp.More()) {
1161  shapes.push_back(TopoShape(xp.Current()));
1162  xp.Next();
1163  }
1164  }
1165  }
1166  if (mapElement == MapElement::map) {
1167  mapSubElementsTo(shapes);

1172 std::vector<TopoShape> TopoShape::getOrderedVertexes(MapElement mapElement) const
1173 {
1174  if (isNull()) {
1175  return std::vector<TopoShape>();
1176  }
1177 
1178  std::vector<TopoShape> shapes;
1179 
1180  auto collect = [&](const TopoDS_Shape& s) {
1181  auto wire = TopoDS::Wire(s);
1182  BRepTools_WireExplorer xp(wire);
1183  while (xp.More()) {
1184  shapes.push_back(TopoShape(xp.CurrentVertex()));
1185  xp.Next();
1186  }
1187  // special treatment for open wires
1188  TopoDS_Vertex Vfirst, Vlast;
1189  TopExp::Vertices(wire, Vfirst, Vlast);
1190  if (!Vfirst.IsNull() && !Vlast.IsNull()) {
1191  if (!Vfirst.IsSame(Vlast)) {
1192  shapes.push_back(TopoShape(Vlast));
1193  }
1194  }
1195  };
1196 
1197  if (shapeType() == TopAbs_WIRE) {
1198  collect(getShape());
1199  }
1200  else {
1201  // INIT_SHAPE_CACHE();
1202  initCache();
1203  for (const auto& s : getSubShapes(TopAbs_WIRE)) {
1204  collect(s);
1205  }
1206  }
1207  if (mapElement == MapElement::map) {
1208  mapSubElementsTo(shapes);
1209  }
1210  return shapes;
1211 }

1247 struct NameKey
1248 {
1249  Data::MappedName name;
1250  long tag = 0;
1251  int shapetype = 0;
1252 
1253  NameKey() = default;
1254  explicit NameKey(Data::MappedName n)
1255  : name(std::move(n))
1256  {}
1257  NameKey(int type, Data::MappedName n)
1258  : name(std::move(n))
1259  {
1260  // Order the shape type from vertex < edge < face < other. We'll rely
1261  // on this for sorting when we name the geometry element.
1262  switch (type) {
1263  case TopAbs_VERTEX:
1264  shapetype = 0;
1265  break;
1266  case TopAbs_EDGE:
1267  shapetype = 1;
1268  break;
1269  case TopAbs_FACE:
1270  shapetype = 2;
1271  break;
1272  default:
1273  shapetype = 3;
1274  }
1275  }
1276  bool operator<(const NameKey& other) const
1277  {
1278  if (shapetype < other.shapetype) {
1279  return true;
1280  }
1281  if (shapetype > other.shapetype) {
1282  return false;
1283  }
1284  if (tag < other.tag) {
1285  return true;
1286  }
1287  if (tag > other.tag) {
1288  return false;
1289  }
1290  return name < other.name;
1291  }
1292 };

1332 // TODO: Refactor checkForParallelOrCoplanar to reduce complexity
1333 void checkForParallelOrCoplanar(const TopoDS_Shape& newShape,
1334  const ShapeInfo& newInfo,
1335  std::vector<TopoDS_Shape>& newShapes,
1336  const gp_Pln& pln,
1337  int& parallelFace,
1338  int& coplanarFace,
1339  int& checkParallel)
1340 {
1341  for (TopExp_Explorer xp(newShape, newInfo.type); xp.More(); xp.Next()) {
1342  newShapes.push_back(xp.Current());
1343 
1344  if ((parallelFace < 0 || coplanarFace < 0) && checkParallel > 0) {
1345  // Specialized checking for high level mapped
1346  // face that are either coplanar or parallel
1347  // with the source face, which are common in
1348  // operations like extrusion. Once found, the
1349  // first coplanar face will assign an index of
1350  // INT_MIN+1, and the first parallel face
1351  // INT_MIN. The purpose of these special
1352  // indexing is to make the name more stable for
1353  // those generated faces.
1354  //
1355  // For example, the top or bottom face of an
1356  // extrusion will be named using the extruding
1357  // face. With a fixed index, the name is no
1358  // longer affected by adding/removing of holes
1359  // inside the extruding face/sketch.
1360  gp_Pln plnOther;
1361  if (TopoShape(newShapes.back()).findPlane(plnOther)) {
1362  if (pln.Axis().IsParallel(plnOther.Axis(), Precision::Angular())) {
1363  if (coplanarFace < 0) {
1364  gp_Vec vec(pln.Axis().Location(), plnOther.Axis().Location());
1365  Standard_Real D1 = gp_Vec(pln.Axis().Direction()).Dot(vec);
1366  if (D1 < 0) {
1367  D1 = -D1;
1368  }
1369  Standard_Real D2 = gp_Vec(plnOther.Axis().Direction()).Dot(vec);
1370  if (D2 < 0) {
1371  D2 = -D2;
1372  }
1373  if (D1 <= Precision::Confusion() && D2 <= Precision::Confusion()) {
1374  coplanarFace = (int)newShapes.size();
1375  continue;
1376  }
1377  }
1378  if (parallelFace < 0) {
1379  parallelFace = (int)newShapes.size();
1380  }
1381  }
1382  }
1383  }
1384  }
1385 }
1386 
1387 // TODO: Refactor makeShapeWithElementMap to reduce complexity
1388 TopoShape& TopoShape::makeShapeWithElementMap(const TopoDS_Shape& shape,
1389  const Mapper& mapper,
1390  const std::vector<TopoShape>& shapes,
1391  const char* op)
1392 {
1393  setShape(shape);
1394  if (shape.IsNull()) {
1395  FC_THROWM(NullShapeException, "Null shape");
1396  }
1397 
1398  if (shapes.empty()) {
1399  return *this;
1400  }
1401 
1402  size_t canMap = 0;
1403  for (auto& incomingShape : shapes) {
1404  if (canMapElement(incomingShape)) {
1405  ++canMap;
1406  }
1407  }
1408  if (canMap == 0U) {
1409  return *this;
1410  }
1411  if (canMap != shapes.size() && FC_LOG_INSTANCE.isEnabled(FC_LOGLEVEL_LOG)) {
1412  FC_WARN("Not all input shapes are mappable"); // NOLINT
1413  }
1414 
1415  if (!op) {
1416  op = Part::OpCodes::Maker;
1417  }
1418  std::string _op = op;
1419  _op += '_';
1420 
1421  initCache();
1422  ShapeInfo vertexInfo(_Shape, TopAbs_VERTEX, _cache->getAncestry(TopAbs_VERTEX));
1423  ShapeInfo edgeInfo(_Shape, TopAbs_EDGE, _cache->getAncestry(TopAbs_EDGE));
1424  ShapeInfo faceInfo(_Shape, TopAbs_FACE, _cache->getAncestry(TopAbs_FACE));
1425  mapSubElement(shapes); // Intentionally leave the op off here
1426 
1427  std::array<ShapeInfo*, 3> infos = {&vertexInfo, &edgeInfo, &faceInfo};
1428 
1429  std::array<ShapeInfo*, TopAbs_SHAPE> infoMap {};
1430  infoMap[TopAbs_VERTEX] = &vertexInfo;
1431  infoMap[TopAbs_EDGE] = &edgeInfo;
1432  infoMap[TopAbs_WIRE] = &edgeInfo;
1433  infoMap[TopAbs_FACE] = &faceInfo;
1434  infoMap[TopAbs_SHELL] = &faceInfo;
1435  infoMap[TopAbs_SOLID] = &faceInfo;
1436  infoMap[TopAbs_COMPOUND] = &faceInfo;
1437  infoMap[TopAbs_COMPSOLID] = &faceInfo;
1438 
1439  std::ostringstream ss;
1440  std::string postfix;
1441  Data::MappedName newName;
1442 
1443  std::map<Data::IndexedName, std::map<NameKey, NameInfo>> newNames;
1444 
1445  // First, collect names from other shapes that generates or modifies the
1446  // new shape
1447  for (auto& pinfo : infos) { // Walk Vertexes, then Edges, then Faces
1448  auto& info = *pinfo;
1449  for (const auto& incomingShape : shapes) {
1450  if (!canMapElement(incomingShape)) {
1451  continue;
1452  }
1453  auto& otherMap = incomingShape._cache->getAncestry(info.type);
1454  if (otherMap.count() == 0) {
1455  continue;
1456  }
1457  for (int i = 1; i <= otherMap.count(); i++) {
1458  const auto& otherElement = otherMap.find(incomingShape._Shape, i);
1459  // Find all new objects that are a modification of the old object
1460  Data::ElementIDRefs sids;
1461  NameKey key(
1462  info.type,
1463  incomingShape.getMappedName(Data::IndexedName::fromConst(info.shapetype, i),
1464  true,
1465  &sids));
1466 
1467  int newShapeCounter = 0;
1468  for (auto& newShape : mapper.modified(otherElement)) {
1469  ++newShapeCounter;
1470  if (newShape.ShapeType() >= TopAbs_SHAPE) {
1471  // NOLINTNEXTLINE
1472  FC_ERR("unknown modified shape type " << newShape.ShapeType() << " from "
1473  << info.shapetype << i);
1474  continue;
1475  }
1476  auto& newInfo = *infoMap.at(newShape.ShapeType());
1477  if (newInfo.type != newShape.ShapeType()) {
1478  if (FC_LOG_INSTANCE.isEnabled(FC_LOGLEVEL_LOG)) {
1479  // TODO: it seems modified shape may report higher
1480  // level shape type just like generated shape below.
1481  // Maybe we shall do the same for name construction.
1482  // NOLINTNEXTLINE
1483  FC_WARN("modified shape type " << shapeName(newShape.ShapeType())
1484  << " mismatch with " << info.shapetype
1485  << i);
1486  }
1487  continue;
1488  }
1489  int newShapeIndex = newInfo.find(newShape);
1490  if (newShapeIndex == 0) {
1491  // This warning occurs in makeElementRevolve. It generates
1492  // some shape from a vertex that never made into the
1493  // final shape. There may be incomingShape cases there.
1494  if (FC_LOG_INSTANCE.isEnabled(FC_LOGLEVEL_LOG)) {
1495  // NOLINTNEXTLINE
1496  FC_WARN("Cannot find " << op << " modified " << newInfo.shapetype
1497  << " from " << info.shapetype << i);
1498  }
1499  continue;
1500  }
1501 
1502  Data::IndexedName element =
1503  Data::IndexedName::fromConst(newInfo.shapetype, newShapeIndex);
1504  if (getMappedName(element)) {
1505  continue;
1506  }
1507 
1508  key.tag = incomingShape.Tag;
1509  auto& name_info = newNames[element][key];
1510  name_info.sids = sids;
1511  name_info.index = newShapeCounter;
1512  name_info.shapetype = info.shapetype;
1513  }
1514 
1515  int checkParallel = -1;
1516  gp_Pln pln;
1517 
1518  // Find all new objects that were generated from an old object
1519  // (e.g. a face generated from an edge)
1520  newShapeCounter = 0;
1521  for (auto& newShape : mapper.generated(otherElement)) {
1522  if (newShape.ShapeType() >= TopAbs_SHAPE) {
1523  // NOLINTNEXTLINE
1524  FC_ERR("unknown generated shape type " << newShape.ShapeType() << " from "
1525  << info.shapetype << i);
1526  continue;
1527  }
1528 
1529  int parallelFace = -1;
1530  int coplanarFace = -1;
1531  auto& newInfo = *infoMap.at(newShape.ShapeType());
1532  std::vector<TopoDS_Shape> newShapes;
1533  int shapeOffset = 0;
1534  if (newInfo.type == newShape.ShapeType()) {
1535  newShapes.push_back(newShape);
1536  }
1537  else {
1538  // It is possible for the maker to report generating a
1539  // higher level shape, such as shell or solid. For
1540  // example, when extruding, OCC will report the
1541  // extruding face generating the entire solid. However,
1542  // it will also report the edges of the extruding face
1543  // generating the side faces. In this case, too much
1544  // information is bad for us. We don't want the name of
1545  // the side face (and its edges) to be coupled with
1546  // incomingShape (unrelated) edges in the extruding face.
1547  //
1548  // shapeOffset below is used to make sure the higher
1549  // level mapped names comes late after sorting. We'll
1550  // ignore those names if there are more precise mapping
1551  // available.
1552  shapeOffset = 3;
1553 
1554  if (info.type == TopAbs_FACE && checkParallel < 0) {
1555  if (!TopoShape(otherElement).findPlane(pln)) {
1556  checkParallel = 0;
1557  }
1558  else {
1559  checkParallel = 1;
1560  }
1561  }
1562  checkForParallelOrCoplanar(newShape,
1563  newInfo,
1564  newShapes,
1565  pln,
1566  parallelFace,
1567  coplanarFace,
1568  checkParallel);
1569  }
1570  key.shapetype += shapeOffset;
1571  for (auto& workingShape : newShapes) {
1572  ++newShapeCounter;
1573  int workingShapeIndex = newInfo.find(workingShape);
1574  if (workingShapeIndex == 0) {
1575  if (FC_LOG_INSTANCE.isEnabled(FC_LOGLEVEL_LOG)) {
1576  // NOLINTNEXTLINE
1577  FC_WARN("Cannot find " << op << " generated " << newInfo.shapetype
1578  << " from " << info.shapetype << i);
1579  }
1580  continue;
1581  }
1582 
1583  Data::IndexedName element =
1584  Data::IndexedName::fromConst(newInfo.shapetype, workingShapeIndex);
1585  auto mapped = getMappedName(element);
1586  if (mapped) {
1587  continue;
1588  }
1589 
1590  key.tag = incomingShape.Tag;
1591  auto& name_info = newNames[element][key];
1592  name_info.sids = sids;
1593  if (newShapeCounter == parallelFace) {
1594  name_info.index = std::numeric_limits<int>::min();
1595  }
1596  else if (newShapeCounter == coplanarFace) {
1597  name_info.index = std::numeric_limits<int>::min() + 1;
1598  }
1599  else {
1600  name_info.index = -newShapeCounter;
1601  }
1602  name_info.shapetype = info.shapetype;
1603  }
1604  key.shapetype -= shapeOffset;
1605  }
1606  }
1607  }
1608  }
1609 
1610  // We shall first exclude those names generated from high level mapping. If
1611  // there are still any unnamed elements left after we go through the process
1612  // below, we set delayed=true, and start using those excluded names.
1613  bool delayed = false;
1614 
1615  while (true) {
1616 
1617  // Construct the names for modification/generation info collected in
1618  // the previous step
1619  for (auto itName = newNames.begin(), itNext = itName; itNext != newNames.end();
1620  itName = itNext) {
1621  // We treat the first modified/generated source shape name specially.
1622  // If case there are more than one source shape. We hash the first
1623  // source name separately, and then obtain the second string id by
1624  // hashing all the source names together. We then use the second
1625  // string id as the postfix for our name.
1626  //
1627  // In this way, we can associate the same source that are modified by
1628  // multiple other shapes.
1629 
1630  ++itNext;
1631 
1632  auto& element = itName->first;
1633  auto& names = itName->second;
1634  const auto& first_key = names.begin()->first;
1635  auto& first_info = names.begin()->second;
1636 
1637  if (!delayed && first_key.shapetype >= 3 && first_info.index > INT_MIN + 1) {
1638  // This name is mapped from high level (shell, solid, etc.)
1639  // Delay till next round.
1640  //
1641  // index>INT_MAX+1 is for checking generated coplanar and
1642  // parallel face mapping, which has special fixed index to make
1643  // name stable. These names are not delayed.
1644  continue;
1645  }
1646  if (!delayed && getMappedName(element)) {
1647  newNames.erase(itName);
1648  continue;
1649  }
1650 
1651  int name_type =
1652  first_info.index > 0 ? 1 : 2; // index>0 means modified, or else generated
1653  Data::MappedName first_name = first_key.name;
1654 
1655  Data::ElementIDRefs sids(first_info.sids);
1656 
1657  postfix.clear();
1658  if (names.size() > 1) {
1659  ss.str("");
1660  ss << '(';
1661  bool first = true;
1662  auto it = names.begin();
1663  int count = 0;
1664  for (++it; it != names.end(); ++it) {
1665  auto& other_key = it->first;
1666  if (other_key.shapetype >= 3 && first_key.shapetype < 3) {
1667  // shapetype>=3 means it's a high level mapping (e.g. a face
1668  // generates a solid). We don't want that if there are more
1669  // precise low level mapping available. See comments above
1670  // for more details.
1671  break;
1672  }
1673  if (first) {
1674  first = false;
1675  }
1676  else {
1677  ss << '|';
1678  }
1679  auto& other_info = it->second;
1680  std::ostringstream ss2;
1681  if (other_info.index != 1) {
1682  // 'K' marks the additional source shape of this
1683  // generate (or modified) shape.
1684  ss2 << elementMapPrefix() << 'K';
1685  if (other_info.index == INT_MIN) {
1686  ss2 << '0';
1687  }
1688  else if (other_info.index == INT_MIN + 1) {
1689  ss2 << "00";
1690  }
1691  else {
1692  // The same source shape may generate or modify
1693  // more than one shape. The index here marks the
1694  // position it is reported by OCC. Including the
1695  // index here is likely to degrade name stablilty,
1696  // but is unfortunately a necessity to avoid
1697  // duplicate names.
1698  ss2 << other_info.index;
1699  }
1700  }
1701  Data::MappedName other_name = other_key.name;
1702 
1703  ensureElementMap()->encodeElementName(*other_info.shapetype,
1704  other_name,
1705  ss2,
1706  &sids,
1707  Tag,
1708  nullptr,
1709  other_key.tag);
1710  ss << other_name;
1711  if ((name_type == 1 && other_info.index < 0)
1712  || (name_type == 2 && other_info.index > 0)) {
1713  if (FC_LOG_INSTANCE.isEnabled(FC_LOGLEVEL_LOG)) {
1714  FC_WARN("element is both generated and modified"); // NOLINT
1715  }
1716  name_type = 0;
1717  }
1718  sids += other_info.sids;
1719  // To avoid the name becoming to long, just put some limit here
1720  if (++count == 4) {
1721  break;
1722  }
1723  }
1724  if (!first) {
1725  ss << ')';
1726  if (Hasher) {
1727  sids.push_back(Hasher->getID(ss.str().c_str()));
1728  ss.str("");
1729  ss << sids.back().toString();
1730  }
1731  postfix = ss.str();
1732  }
1733  }
1734 
1735  ss.str("");
1736  if (name_type == 2) {
1737  ss << genPostfix();
1738  }
1739  else if (name_type == 1) {
1740  ss << modPostfix();
1741  }
1742  else {
1743  ss << modgenPostfix();
1744  }
1745  if (first_info.index == INT_MIN) {
1746  ss << '0';
1747  }
1748  else if (first_info.index == INT_MIN + 1) {
1749  ss << "00";
1750  }
1751  else if (abs(first_info.index) > 1) {
1752  ss << abs(first_info.index);
1753  }
1754  ss << postfix;
1755 
1756  ensureElementMap()
1757  ->encodeElementName(element[0], first_name, ss, &sids, Tag, op, first_key.tag);
1758  elementMap()->setElementName(element, first_name, Tag, &sids);
1759  if (!delayed && first_key.shapetype < 3) {
1760  newNames.erase(itName);
1761  }
1762  }
1763 
1764  // The reverse pass. Starting from the highest level element, i.e.
1765  // Face, for any element that are named, assign names for its lower unnamed
1766  // elements. For example, if Edge1 is named E1, and its vertexes are not
1767  // named, then name them as E1;U1, E1;U2, etc.
1768  //
1769  // In order to make the name as stable as possible, we may assign multiple
1770  // names (which must be sorted, because we may use the first one to name
1771  // upper element in the final pass) to lower element if it appears in
1772  // multiple higher elements, e.g. same edge in multiple faces.
1773 
1774  for (size_t infoIndex = infos.size() - 1; infoIndex != 0; --infoIndex) {
1775  std::map<Data::IndexedName,
1776  std::map<Data::MappedName, NameInfo, Data::ElementNameComparator>>
1777  names;
1778  auto& info = *infos.at(infoIndex);
1779  auto& next = *infos.at(infoIndex - 1);
1780  int elementCounter = 1;
1781  auto it = newNames.end();
1782  if (delayed) {
1783  it = newNames.upper_bound(Data::IndexedName::fromConst(info.shapetype, 0));
1784  }
1785  for (;; ++elementCounter) {
1786  Data::IndexedName element;
1787  if (!delayed) {
1788  if (elementCounter > info.count()) {
1789  break;
1790  }
1791  element = Data::IndexedName::fromConst(info.shapetype, elementCounter);
1792  if (newNames.count(element) != 0U) {
1793  continue;
1794  }
1795  }
1796  else if (it == newNames.end()
1797  || !boost::starts_with(it->first.getType(), info.shapetype)) {
1798  break;
1799  }
1800  else {
1801  element = it->first;
1802  ++it;
1803  elementCounter = element.getIndex();
1804  if (elementCounter == 0 || elementCounter > info.count()) {
1805  continue;
1806  }
1807  }
1808  Data::ElementIDRefs sids;
1809  Data::MappedName mapped = getMappedName(element, false, &sids);
1810  if (!mapped) {
1811  continue;
1812  }
1813 
1814  TopTools_IndexedMapOfShape submap;
1815  TopExp::MapShapes(info.find(elementCounter), next.type, submap);
1816  for (int submapIndex = 1, infoCounter = 1; submapIndex <= submap.Extent();
1817  ++submapIndex) {
1818  ss.str("");
1819  int elementIndex = next.find(submap(submapIndex));
1820  assert(elementIndex);
1821  Data::IndexedName indexedName =
1822  Data::IndexedName::fromConst(next.shapetype, elementIndex);
1823  if (getMappedName(indexedName)) {
1824  continue;
1825  }
1826  auto& infoRef = names[indexedName][mapped];
1827  infoRef.index = infoCounter++;
1828  infoRef.sids = sids;
1829  }
1830  }
1831  // Assign the actual names
1832  for (auto& [indexedName, nameInfoMap] : names) {
1833  // Do we really want multiple names for an element in this case?
1834  // If not, we just pick the name in the first sorting order here.
1835  auto& nameInfoMapEntry = *nameInfoMap.begin();
1836  {
1837  auto& nameInfo = nameInfoMapEntry.second;
1838  auto& sids = nameInfo.sids;
1839  newName = nameInfoMapEntry.first;
1840  ss.str("");
1841  ss << upperPostfix();
1842  if (nameInfo.index > 1) {
1843  ss << nameInfo.index;
1844  }
1845 
1846  ensureElementMap()->encodeElementName(indexedName[0], newName, ss, &sids, Tag, op);
1847  elementMap()->setElementName(indexedName, newName, Tag, &sids);
1848  }
1849  }
1850  }
1851 
1852  // The forward pass. For any elements that are not named, try construct its
1853  // name from the lower elements
1854  bool hasUnnamed = false;
1855  for (size_t ifo = 1; ifo < infos.size(); ++ifo) {
1856  auto& info = *infos.at(ifo);
1857  auto& prev = *infos.at(ifo - 1);
1858  for (int i = 1; i <= info.count(); ++i) {
1859  Data::IndexedName element = Data::IndexedName::fromConst(info.shapetype, i);
1860  if (getMappedName(element)) {
1861  continue;
1862  }
1863 
1864  Data::ElementIDRefs sids;
1865  std::map<Data::MappedName, Data::IndexedName, Data::ElementNameComparator> names;
1866  TopExp_Explorer xp;
1867  if (info.type == TopAbs_FACE) {
1868  xp.Init(BRepTools::OuterWire(TopoDS::Face(info.find(i))), TopAbs_EDGE);
1869  }
1870  else {
1871  xp.Init(info.find(i), prev.type);
1872  }
1873  for (; xp.More(); xp.Next()) {
1874  int previousElementIndex = prev.find(xp.Current());
1875  assert(previousElementIndex);
1876  Data::IndexedName prevElement =
1877  Data::IndexedName::fromConst(prev.shapetype, previousElementIndex);
1878  if (!delayed && (newNames.count(prevElement) != 0U)) {
1879  names.clear();
1880  break;
1881  }
1882  Data::ElementIDRefs sid;
1883  Data::MappedName name = getMappedName(prevElement, false, &sid);
1884  if (!name) {
1885  // only assign name if all lower elements are named
1886  if (FC_LOG_INSTANCE.isEnabled(FC_LOGLEVEL_LOG)) {
1887  FC_WARN("unnamed lower element " << prevElement); // NOLINT
1888  }
1889  names.clear();
1890  break;
1891  }
1892  auto res = names.emplace(name, prevElement);
1893  if (res.second) {
1894  sids += sid;
1895  }
1896  else if (prevElement != res.first->second) {
1897  // The seam edge will appear twice, which is normal. We
1898  // only warn if the mapped element names are different.
1899  // NOLINTNEXTLINE
1900  FC_WARN("lower element " << prevElement << " and " << res.first->second
1901  << " has duplicated name " << name << " for "
1902  << info.shapetype << i);
1903  }
1904  }
1905  if (names.empty()) {
1906  hasUnnamed = true;
1907  continue;
1908  }
1909  auto it = names.begin();
1910  newName = it->first;
1911  if (names.size() == 1) {
1912  ss << lowerPostfix();
1913  }
1914  else {
1915  bool first = true;
1916  ss.str("");
1917  if (!Hasher) {
1918  ss << lowerPostfix();
1919  }
1920  ss << '(';
1921  int count = 0;
1922  for (++it; it != names.end(); ++it) {
1923  if (first) {
1924  first = false;
1925  }
1926  else {
1927  ss << '|';
1928  }
1929  ss << it->first;
1930 
1931  // To avoid the name becoming to long, just put some limit here
1932  if (++count == 4) {
1933  break;
1934  }
1935  }
1936  ss << ')';
1937  if (Hasher) {
1938  sids.push_back(Hasher->getID(ss.str().c_str()));
1939  ss.str("");
1940  ss << lowerPostfix() << sids.back().toString();
1941  }
1942  }
1943 
1944  ensureElementMap()->encodeElementName(element[0], newName, ss, &sids, Tag, op);
1945  elementMap()->setElementName(element, newName, Tag, &sids);
1946  }
1947  }
1948  if (!hasUnnamed || delayed || newNames.empty()) {
1949  break;
1950  }
1951  delayed = true;
1952  }
1953  return *this;
1954 }

1956 namespace
1957 {
1958 void addShapesToBuilder(const std::vector<TopoShape>& shapes,
1959  BRep_Builder& builder,
1960  TopoDS_Compound& comp)
1961 {
1962  int count = 0;
1963  for (auto& topoShape : shapes) {
1964  if (topoShape.isNull()) {
1965  FC_WARN("Null input shape"); // NOLINT
1966  continue;
1967  }
1968  builder.Add(comp, topoShape.getShape());
1969  ++count;
1970  }
1971  if (count == 0) {
1972  FC_THROWM(NullShapeException, "Null shape");
1973  }
1974 }

1977 // TODO: Can this be consolidated with getSubShape()? Empty Parm Logic is a little different.
1978 TopoShape TopoShape::getSubTopoShape(const char* Type, bool silent) const
1979 {
1980  if (!Type || !Type[0]) {
1981  switch (shapeType(true)) {
1982  case TopAbs_COMPOUND:
1983  case TopAbs_COMPSOLID:
1984  if (countSubShapes(TopAbs_SOLID) == 1) {
1985  return getSubTopoShape(TopAbs_SOLID, 1);
1986  }
1987  if (countSubShapes(TopAbs_SHELL) == 1) {
1988  return getSubTopoShape(TopAbs_SHELL, 1);
1989  }
1990  if (countSubShapes(TopAbs_FACE) == 1) {
1991  return getSubTopoShape(TopAbs_FACE, 1);
1992  }
1993  if (countSubShapes(TopAbs_WIRE) == 1) {
1994  return getSubTopoShape(TopAbs_WIRE, 1);
1995  }
1996  if (countSubShapes(TopAbs_EDGE) == 1) {
1997  return getSubTopoShape(TopAbs_EDGE, 1);
1998  }
1999  if (countSubShapes(TopAbs_VERTEX) == 1) {
2000  return getSubTopoShape(TopAbs_VERTEX, 1);
2001  }
2002  break;
2003  default:
2004  break;
2005  }
2006  return *this;
2007  }
2008 
2009  Data::MappedElement mapped = getElementName(Type);
2010  if (!mapped.index && boost::starts_with(Type, elementMapPrefix())) {
2011  if (!silent) {
2012  FC_THROWM(Base::CADKernelError, "Mapped element not found: " << Type);
2013  }
2014  return TopoShape();
2015  }
2016  auto res = shapeTypeAndIndex(mapped.index);
2017  if (res.second <= 0) {
2018  if (!silent) {
2019  FC_THROWM(Base::ValueError, "Invalid shape name " << (Type ? Type : ""));
2020  }
2021  return TopoShape();
2022  }
2023  return getSubTopoShape(res.first, res.second, silent);
2024 }

2060 TopoShape& TopoShape::makeElementEvolve(const TopoShape& spine,

2143 TopoShape& TopoShape::makeElementRuledSurface(const std::vector<TopoShape>& shapes,
2144  int orientation,
2145  const char* op)
2146 {
2147  if (!op) {
2148  op = Part::OpCodes::RuledSurface;
2149  }
2150 
2151  if (shapes.size() != 2) {
2152  FC_THROWM(Base::CADKernelError, "Wrong number of input shapes");
2153  }
2154 
2155  std::vector<TopoShape> curves(2);
2156  int i = 0;
2157  for (auto& s : shapes) {
2158  if (s.isNull()) {
2159  FC_THROWM(NullShapeException, "Null input shape");
2160  }
2161  auto type = s.shapeType();
2162  if (type == TopAbs_WIRE || type == TopAbs_EDGE) {
2163  curves[i++] = s;
2164  continue;
2165  }
2166  auto countOfWires = s.countSubShapes(TopAbs_WIRE);
2167  if (countOfWires > 1) {
2168  curves[i++] = s.getSubTopoShape(TopAbs_WIRE, 1);
2169  continue;
2170  }
2171  auto countOfEdges = s.countSubShapes(TopAbs_EDGE);
2172  if (countOfEdges == 0) {
2173  FC_THROWM(Base::CADKernelError, "Input shape has no edge");
2174  }
2175  if (countOfEdges == 1) {
2176  curves[i++] = s.getSubTopoShape(TopAbs_EDGE, 1);
2177  continue;
2178  }
2179  curves[i] = s.makeElementWires();
2180  if (curves[i].isNull()) {
2181  FC_THROWM(NullShapeException, "Null input shape");
2182  }
2183  if (curves[i].shapeType() != TopAbs_WIRE) {
2184  FC_THROWM(Base::CADKernelError, "Input shape forms more than one wire");
2185  }
2186  ++i;
2187  }
2188 
2189  if (curves[0].shapeType() != curves[1].shapeType()) {
2190  for (auto& curve : curves) {
2191  if (curve.shapeType() == TopAbs_EDGE) {
2192  curve = curve.makeElementWires();
2193  }
2194  }
2195  }
2196 
2197  auto& S1 = curves[0];
2198  auto& S2 = curves[1];
2199  bool isWire = S1.shapeType() == TopAbs_WIRE;
2200 
2201  // https://forum.freecadweb.org/viewtopic.php?f=8&t=24052
2202  //
2203  // if both shapes are sub-elements of one common shape then the fill
2204  // algorithm leads to problems if the shape has set a placement. The
2205  // workaround is to copy the sub-shape
2206  S1 = S1.makeElementCopy();
2207  S2 = S2.makeElementCopy();
2208 
2209  if (orientation == 0) {
2210  // Automatic
2211  Handle(Adaptor3d_HCurve) a1;
2212  Handle(Adaptor3d_HCurve) a2;
2213  if (!isWire) {
2214  BRepAdaptor_HCurve adapt1(TopoDS::Edge(S1.getShape()));
2215  BRepAdaptor_HCurve adapt2(TopoDS::Edge(S2.getShape()));
2216  a1 = new BRepAdaptor_HCurve(adapt1);
2217  a2 = new BRepAdaptor_HCurve(adapt2);
2218  }
2219  else {
2220  BRepAdaptor_HCompCurve adapt1(TopoDS::Wire(S1.getShape()));
2221  BRepAdaptor_HCompCurve adapt2(TopoDS::Wire(S2.getShape()));
2222  a1 = new BRepAdaptor_HCompCurve(adapt1);
2223  a2 = new BRepAdaptor_HCompCurve(adapt2);
2224  }
2225 
2226  if (!a1.IsNull() && !a2.IsNull()) {
2227  // get end points of 1st curve
2228  gp_Pnt p1 = a1->Value(0.9 * a1->FirstParameter() + 0.1 * a1->LastParameter());
2229  gp_Pnt p2 = a1->Value(0.1 * a1->FirstParameter() + 0.9 * a1->LastParameter());
2230  if (S1.getShape().Orientation() == TopAbs_REVERSED) {
2231  std::swap(p1, p2);
2232  }
2233 
2234  // get end points of 2nd curve
2235  gp_Pnt p3 = a2->Value(0.9 * a2->FirstParameter() + 0.1 * a2->LastParameter());
2236  gp_Pnt p4 = a2->Value(0.1 * a2->FirstParameter() + 0.9 * a2->LastParameter());
2237  if (S2.getShape().Orientation() == TopAbs_REVERSED) {
2238  std::swap(p3, p4);
2239  }
2240 
2241  // Form two triangles (P1,P2,P3) and (P4,P3,P2) and check their normals.
2242  // If the dot product is negative then it's assumed that the resulting face
2243  // is twisted, hence the 2nd edge is reversed.
2244  gp_Vec v1(p1, p2);
2245  gp_Vec v2(p1, p3);
2246  gp_Vec n1 = v1.Crossed(v2);
2247 
2248  gp_Vec v3(p4, p3);
2249  gp_Vec v4(p4, p2);
2250  gp_Vec n2 = v3.Crossed(v4);
2251 
2252  if (n1.Dot(n2) < 0) {
2253  S2.setShape(S2.getShape().Reversed(), false);
2254  }
2255  }
2256  }
2257  else if (orientation == 2) {
2258  // Reverse
2259  S2.setShape(S2.getShape().Reversed(), false);
2260  }
2261 
2262  TopoDS_Shape ruledShape;
2263  if (!isWire) {
2264  ruledShape = BRepFill::Face(TopoDS::Edge(S1.getShape()), TopoDS::Edge(S2.getShape()));
2265  }
2266  else {
2267  ruledShape = BRepFill::Shell(TopoDS::Wire(S1.getShape()), TopoDS::Wire(S2.getShape()));
2268  }
2269 
2270  // Both BRepFill::Face() and Shell() modifies the original input edges
2271  // without any API to provide relationship to the output edges. So we have
2272  // to use searchSubShape() to build the relationship by ourselves.
2273 
2274  TopoShape res(ruledShape.Located(TopLoc_Location()));
2275  std::vector<TopoShape> edges;
2276  for (const auto& c : curves) {
2277  for (const auto& e : c.getSubTopoShapes(TopAbs_EDGE)) {
2278  auto found = res.findSubShapesWithSharedVertex(e);
2279  if (found.size() > 0) {
2280  found.front().resetElementMap(e.elementMap());
2281  edges.push_back(found.front());
2282  }
2283  }
2284  }
2285  // Use empty mapper and let makeShapeWithElementMap name the created surface with lower
2286  // elements.
2287  return makeShapeWithElementMap(res.getShape(), Mapper(), edges, op);
2288 }

2315 static std::vector<TopoShape> prepareProfiles(const std::vector<TopoShape>& shapes,
2316  size_t offset = 0)
2317 {
2318  std::vector<TopoShape> ret;
2319  for (size_t i = offset; i < shapes.size(); ++i) {
2320  auto shape = shapes[i];
2321  if (shape.isNull()) {
2322  FC_THROWM(NullShapeException, "Null input shape");
2323  }
2324  if (shape.countSubShapes(TopAbs_FACE) == 1) {
2325  shape = shape.getSubTopoShape(TopAbs_FACE, 1).splitWires();
2326  }
2327  else if (shape.countSubShapes(TopAbs_WIRE) == 0 && shape.countSubShapes(TopAbs_EDGE) > 0) {
2328  shape = shape.makeElementWires();
2329  }
2330 
2331  if (shape.countSubShapes(TopAbs_WIRE) == 1) {
2332  ret.push_back(shape.getSubTopoShape(TopAbs_WIRE, 1));
2333  continue;
2334  }
2335  else if (shape.countSubShapes(TopAbs_VERTEX) == 1) {
2336  ret.push_back(shape.getSubTopoShape(TopAbs_VERTEX, 1));
2337  continue;
2338  }
2339 
2340  FC_THROWM(Base::CADKernelError,
2341  "Profile shape is not a single vertex, edge, wire nor face.");
2342  }
2343  if (ret.empty()) {
2344  FC_THROWM(Base::CADKernelError, "No profile");
2345  }
2346  return ret;
2347 }

2420 TopoShape& TopoShape::makeElementOffset(const TopoShape& shape,
2421  double offset,
2422  double tol,
2423  bool intersection,
2424  bool selfInter,
2425  short offsetMode,
2426  JoinType join,
2427  FillType fill,
2428  const char* op)
2429 {
2430  if (!op) {
2431  op = Part::OpCodes::Offset;
2432  }
2433 
2434  BRepOffsetAPI_MakeOffsetShape mkOffset;
2435  mkOffset.PerformByJoin(shape.getShape(),
2436  offset,
2437  tol,
2438  BRepOffset_Mode(offsetMode),
2439  intersection ? Standard_True : Standard_False,
2440  selfInter ? Standard_True : Standard_False,
2441  GeomAbs_JoinType(join));
2442 
2443  if (!mkOffset.IsDone()) {
2444  FC_THROWM(Base::CADKernelError, "BRepOffsetAPI_MakeOffsetShape not done");
2445  }
2446 
2447  TopoShape res(Tag, Hasher);
2448  res.makeElementShape(mkOffset, shape, op);
2449  if (shape.hasSubShape(TopAbs_SOLID) && !res.hasSubShape(TopAbs_SOLID)) {
2450  try {
2451  res = res.makeElementSolid();
2452  }
2453  catch (Standard_Failure& e) {
2454  FC_WARN("failed to make solid: " << e.GetMessageString());
2455  }
2456  }
2457  if (fill == FillType::noFill) {
2458  *this = res;
2459  return *this;
2460  }
2461 
2462  // get perimeter wire of original shape.
2463  // Wires returned seem to have edges in connection order.
2464  ShapeAnalysis_FreeBoundsProperties freeCheck(shape.getShape());
2465  freeCheck.Perform();
2466  if (freeCheck.NbClosedFreeBounds() < 1) {
2467  FC_THROWM(Base::CADKernelError, "no closed bounds");
2468  }
2469 
2470  BRep_Builder builder;
2471  std::vector<TopoShape> shapes;
2472  for (int index = 1; index <= freeCheck.NbClosedFreeBounds(); ++index) {
2473  TopoShape originalWire(shape.Tag,
2474  shape.Hasher,
2475  freeCheck.ClosedFreeBound(index)->FreeBound());
2476  originalWire.mapSubElement(shape);
2477  const BRepAlgo_Image& img = mkOffset.MakeOffset().OffsetEdgesFromShapes();
2478 
2479  // build offset wire.
2480  TopoDS_Wire offsetWire;
2481  builder.MakeWire(offsetWire);
2482  for (const auto& s : originalWire.getSubShapes(TopAbs_EDGE)) {
2483  if (!img.HasImage(s)) {
2484  FC_THROWM(Base::CADKernelError, "no image for shape");
2485  }
2486  const TopTools_ListOfShape& currentImage = img.Image(s);
2487  TopTools_ListIteratorOfListOfShape listIt;
2488  int edgeCount(0);
2489  TopoDS_Edge mappedEdge;
2490  for (listIt.Initialize(currentImage); listIt.More(); listIt.Next()) {
2491  if (listIt.Value().ShapeType() != TopAbs_EDGE) {
2492  continue;
2493  }
2494  edgeCount++;
2495  mappedEdge = TopoDS::Edge(listIt.Value());
2496  }
2497 
2498  if (edgeCount != 1) {
2499  std::ostringstream stream;
2500  stream << "wrong edge count: " << edgeCount << std::endl;
2501  FC_THROWM(Base::CADKernelError, stream.str().c_str());
2502  }
2503  builder.Add(offsetWire, mappedEdge);
2504  }
2505  std::vector<TopoShape> wires;
2506  wires.push_back(originalWire);
2507  wires.push_back(TopoShape(Tag, Hasher, offsetWire));
2508  wires.back().mapSubElement(res);
2509 
2510  // It would be nice if we could get thruSections to build planar faces
2511  // in all areas possible, so we could run through refine. I tried setting
2512  // ruled to standard_true, but that didn't have the desired affect.
2513  BRepOffsetAPI_ThruSections aGenerator;
2514  aGenerator.AddWire(TopoDS::Wire(originalWire.getShape()));
2515  aGenerator.AddWire(offsetWire);
2516  aGenerator.Build();
2517  if (!aGenerator.IsDone()) {
2518  FC_THROWM(Base::CADKernelError, "ThruSections failed");
2519  }
2520 
2521  shapes.push_back(TopoShape(Tag, Hasher).makeElementShape(aGenerator, wires));
2522  }
2523 
2524  TopoShape perimeterCompound(Tag, Hasher);
2525  perimeterCompound.makeElementCompound(shapes, op);
2526 
2527  // still had to sew. not using the passed in parameter for sew.
2528  // Sew has it's own default tolerance. Opinions?
2529  BRepBuilderAPI_Sewing sewTool;
2530  sewTool.Add(shape.getShape());
2531  sewTool.Add(perimeterCompound.getShape());
2532  sewTool.Add(res.getShape());
2533  sewTool.Perform(); // Perform Sewing
2534 
2535  TopoDS_Shape outputShape = sewTool.SewedShape();
2536  if ((outputShape.ShapeType() == TopAbs_SHELL) && (outputShape.Closed())) {
2537  BRepBuilderAPI_MakeSolid solidMaker(TopoDS::Shell(outputShape));
2538  if (solidMaker.IsDone()) {
2539  TopoDS_Solid temp = solidMaker.Solid();
2540  // contrary to the occ docs the return value OrientCloseSolid doesn't
2541  // indicate whether the shell was open or not. It returns true with an
2542  // open shell and we end up with an invalid solid.
2543  if (BRepLib::OrientClosedSolid(temp)) {
2544  outputShape = temp;
2545  }
2546  }
2547  }
2548 
2549  shapes.clear();
2550  shapes.push_back(shape);
2551  shapes.push_back(res);
2552  shapes.push_back(perimeterCompound);
2553  *this = TopoShape(Tag, Hasher)
2554  .makeShapeWithElementMap(outputShape, MapperSewing(sewTool), shapes, op);
2555  return *this;
2556 }

2558 TopoShape& TopoShape::makeElementOffsetFace(const TopoShape& shape,

2597  outerWire = outerWire.makeElementOffset2D(offset,
2598  joinType,
2599  FillType::noFill,
2600  OpenResult::noOpenResult,
2601  false,
2602  op);
2603  }
2604 
2605  if (std::abs(innerOffset) > Precision::Confusion()) {
2606  TopoShape innerWires(0, Hasher);
2607  innerWires.makeElementCompound(wires,
2608  "",
2609  SingleShapeCompoundCreationPolicy::returnShape);
2610  innerWires = innerWires.makeElementOffset2D(innerOffset,
2611  innerJoinType,
2612  FillType::noFill,
2613  OpenResult::noOpenResult,
2614  true,
2615  op);
2616  wires = innerWires.getSubTopoShapes(TopAbs_WIRE);
2617  }
2618  wires.push_back(outerWire);
2619  gp_Pln pln;
2620  res.push_back(TopoShape(0, Hasher).makeElementFace(wires,
2621  nullptr,
2622  nullptr,
2623  face.findPlane(pln) ? &pln : nullptr));
2624  }
2625  return makeElementCompound(res, "", SingleShapeCompoundCreationPolicy::returnShape);
2626 }

2628 TopoShape& TopoShape::makeElementOffset2D(const TopoShape& shape,
2629  double offset,
2630  JoinType joinType,
2631  FillType fill,
2632  OpenResult allowOpenResult,
2633  bool intersection,
2634  const char* op)
2635 {
2636  if (!op) {
2637  op = Part::OpCodes::Offset2D;
2638  }
2639 
2640  if (shape.isNull()) {
2641  FC_THROWM(Base::ValueError, "makeOffset2D: input shape is null!");
2642  }
2643  if (allowOpenResult == OpenResult::allowOpenResult && OCC_VERSION_HEX < 0x060900) {
2644  FC_THROWM(Base::AttributeError, "openResult argument is not supported on OCC < 6.9.0.");
2645  }
2646 
2647  // OUTLINE OF MAKEOFFSET2D
2648  // * Prepare shapes to process
2649  // ** if _Shape is a compound, recursively call this routine for all subcompounds
2650  // ** if intrsection, dump all non-compound children into shapes to process; otherwise call this
2651  // routine recursively for all children
2652  // ** if _shape isn't a compound, dump it straight to shapes to process
2653  // * Test for shape types, and convert them all to wires
2654  // * find plane
2655  // * OCC call (BRepBuilderAPI_MakeOffset)
2656  // * postprocessing (facemaking):
2657  // ** convert offset result back to faces, if inputs were faces
2658  // ** OR do offset filling:
2659  // *** for closed wires, simply feed source wires + offset wires to smart facemaker
2660  // *** for open wires, try to connect source anf offset result by creating new edges (incomplete
2661  // implementation)
2662  // ** actual call to FaceMakerBullseye, unified for all facemaking.
2663 
2664  std::vector<TopoShape> shapesToProcess;
2665  std::vector<TopoShape> shapesToReturn;
2666  SingleShapeCompoundCreationPolicy outputPolicy = SingleShapeCompoundCreationPolicy::returnShape;
2667  if (shape.getShape().ShapeType() == TopAbs_COMPOUND) {
2668  if (!intersection) {
2669  // simply recursively process the children, independently
2670  expandCompound(shape, shapesToProcess);
2671  outputPolicy = SingleShapeCompoundCreationPolicy::forceCompound;
2672  }
2673  else {
2674  // collect non-compounds from this compound for collective offset. Process other shapes
2675  // independently.
2676  for (auto& s : shape.getSubTopoShapes()) {
2677  if (s.getShape().ShapeType() == TopAbs_COMPOUND) {
2678  // recursively process subcompounds
2679  shapesToReturn.push_back(TopoShape(Tag, Hasher)
2680  .makeElementOffset2D(s,
2681  offset,
2682  joinType,
2683  fill,
2684  allowOpenResult,
2685  intersection,
2686  op));
2687  outputPolicy = SingleShapeCompoundCreationPolicy::forceCompound;
2688  }
2689  else {
2690  shapesToProcess.push_back(s);
2691  }
2692  }
2693  }
2694  }
2695  else {
2696  shapesToProcess.push_back(shape);
2697  }
2698 
2699  if (shapesToProcess.size() > 0) {
2700  TopoShape res(Tag, Hasher);
2701 
2702  // although 2d offset supports offsetting a face directly, it seems there is
2703  // no way to do a collective offset of multiple faces. So, we are doing it
2704  // by getting all wires from the faces, and applying offsets to them, and
2705  // reassembling the faces later.
2706  std::vector<TopoShape> sourceWires;
2707  bool haveWires = false;
2708  bool haveFaces = false;
2709  for (auto& s : shapesToProcess) {
2710  const auto& sh = s.getShape();
2711  switch (sh.ShapeType()) {
2712  case TopAbs_EDGE:
2713  sourceWires.push_back(s.makeElementWires());
2714  haveWires = true;
2715  break;
2716  case TopAbs_WIRE:
2717  sourceWires.push_back(s);
2718  haveWires = true;
2719  break;
2720  case TopAbs_FACE: {
2721  auto outerWire = s.splitWires(&sourceWires);
2722  sourceWires.push_back(outerWire);
2723  haveFaces = true;
2724  } break;
2725  default:
2726  FC_THROWM(Base::TypeError,
2727  "makeOffset2D: input shape is not an edge, wire or face or compound "
2728  "of those.");
2729  break;
2730  }
2731  }
2732  if (haveWires && haveFaces) {
2733  FC_THROWM(
2734  Base::TypeError,
2735  "makeOffset2D: collective offset of a mix of wires and faces is not supported");
2736  }
2737  if (haveFaces) {
2738  allowOpenResult = OpenResult::noOpenResult;
2739  }
2740 
2741  // find plane.
2742  gp_Pln workingPlane;
2743  if (!TopoShape()
2744  .makeElementCompound(sourceWires,
2745  "",
2746  SingleShapeCompoundCreationPolicy::returnShape)
2747  .findPlane(workingPlane)) {
2748  FC_THROWM(Base::CADKernelError, "makeOffset2D: wires are nonplanar or noncoplanar");
2749  }
2750 
2751  // do the offset..
2752  TopoShape offsetShape;
2753  if (fabs(offset) > Precision::Confusion()) {
2754  BRepOffsetAPI_MakeOffsetFix mkOffset(GeomAbs_JoinType(joinType),
2755  allowOpenResult == OpenResult::allowOpenResult);
2756  for (auto& w : sourceWires) {
2757  mkOffset.AddWire(TopoDS::Wire(w.getShape()));
2758  }
2759  try {
2760 #if defined(__GNUC__) && defined(FC_OS_LINUX)
2761  Base::SignalException se;
2762 #endif
2763  mkOffset.Perform(offset);
2764  }
2765  catch (Standard_Failure&) {
2766  throw;
2767  }
2768  catch (...) {
2769  FC_THROWM(Base::CADKernelError,
2770  "BRepOffsetAPI_MakeOffset has crashed! (Unknown exception caught)");
2771  }
2772  if (mkOffset.Shape().IsNull()) {
2773  FC_THROWM(NullShapeException, "makeOffset2D: result of offsetting is null!");
2774  }
2775 
2776  // Copying shape to fix strange orientation behavior, OCC7.0.0. See bug #2699
2777  // http://www.freecadweb.org/tracker/view.php?id=2699
2778  offsetShape = shape.makeElementShape(mkOffset, op).makeElementCopy();
2779  }
2780  else {
2781  offsetShape = TopoShape(Tag, Hasher)
2782  .makeElementCompound(sourceWires,
2783  0,
2784  SingleShapeCompoundCreationPolicy::returnShape);
2785  }
2786 
2787  std::vector<TopoShape> offsetWires;
2788  // interestingly, if wires are removed, empty compounds are returned by MakeOffset (as of
2789  // OCC 7.0.0) so, we just extract all nesting
2790  expandCompound(offsetShape, offsetWires);
2791  if (offsetWires.empty()) {
2792  FC_THROWM(Base::CADKernelError, "makeOffset2D: offset result has no wires.");
2793  }
2794 
2795  std::vector<TopoShape> wiresForMakingFaces;
2796  if (fill == FillType::noFill) {
2797  if (haveFaces) {
2798  wiresForMakingFaces.insert(wiresForMakingFaces.end(),
2799  offsetWires.begin(),
2800  offsetWires.end());
2801  }
2802  else {
2803  shapesToReturn.insert(shapesToReturn.end(), offsetWires.begin(), offsetWires.end());
2804  }
2805  }
2806  else {
2807  // fill offset
2808  if (fabs(offset) < Precision::Confusion()) {
2809  FC_THROWM(Base::ValueError,
2810  "makeOffset2D: offset distance is zero. Can't fill offset.");
2811  }
2812 
2813  // filling offset. There are three major cases to consider:
2814  // 1. source wires and result wires are closed (simplest) -> make face
2815  // from source wire + offset wire
2816  //
2817  // 2. source wire is open, but offset wire is closed (if not
2818  // allowOpenResult). -> throw away source wire and make face right from
2819  // offset result.
2820  //
2821  // 3. source and offset wire are both open (note that there may be
2822  // closed islands in offset result) -> need connecting offset result to
2823  // source wire with new edges
2824 
2825  // first, lets split apart closed and open wires.
2826  std::vector<TopoShape> closedWires;
2827  std::vector<TopoShape> openWires;
2828  for (auto& w : sourceWires) {
2829  if (BRep_Tool::IsClosed(TopoDS::Wire(w.getShape()))) {
2830  closedWires.push_back(w);
2831  }
2832  else {
2833  openWires.push_back(w);
2834  }
2835  }
2836  for (auto& w : offsetWires) {
2837  if (BRep_Tool::IsClosed(TopoDS::Wire(w.getShape()))) {
2838  closedWires.push_back(w);
2839  }
2840  else {
2841  openWires.push_back(w);
2842  }
2843  }
2844 
2845  wiresForMakingFaces.insert(wiresForMakingFaces.end(),
2846  closedWires.begin(),
2847  closedWires.end());
2848  if (allowOpenResult == OpenResult::noOpenResult || openWires.size() == 0) {
2849  // just ignore all open wires
2850  }
2851  else {
2852  // We need to connect open wires to form closed wires.
2853 
2854  // for now, only support offsetting one open wire -> there should be exactly two
2855  // open wires for connecting
2856  if (openWires.size() != 2) {
2857  FC_THROWM(Base::CADKernelError,
2858  "makeOffset2D: collective offset with filling of multiple wires is "
2859  "not supported yet.");
2860  }
2861 
2862  TopoShape openWire1 = openWires.front();
2863  TopoShape openWire2 = openWires.back();
2864 
2865  // find open vertices
2866  BRepTools_WireExplorer xp;
2867  xp.Init(TopoDS::Wire(openWire1.getShape()));
2868  TopoDS_Vertex v1 = xp.CurrentVertex();
2869  for (; xp.More(); xp.Next()) {};
2870  TopoDS_Vertex v2 = xp.CurrentVertex();
2871 
2872  // find open vertices
2873  xp.Init(TopoDS::Wire(openWire2.getShape()));
2874  TopoDS_Vertex v3 = xp.CurrentVertex();
2875  for (; xp.More(); xp.Next()) {};
2876  TopoDS_Vertex v4 = xp.CurrentVertex();
2877 
2878  // check
2879  if (v1.IsNull()) {
2880  FC_THROWM(NullShapeException, "v1 is null");
2881  }
2882  if (v2.IsNull()) {
2883  FC_THROWM(NullShapeException, "v2 is null");
2884  }
2885  if (v3.IsNull()) {
2886  FC_THROWM(NullShapeException, "v3 is null");
2887  }
2888  if (v4.IsNull()) {
2889  FC_THROWM(NullShapeException, "v4 is null");
2890  }
2891 
2892  // assemble new wire
2893 
2894  // we want the connection order to be
2895  // v1 -> openWire1 -> v2 -> (new edge) -> v4 -> openWire2(rev) -> v3 -> (new edge)
2896  // -> v1 let's check if it's the case. If not, we reverse one wire and swap its
2897  // endpoints.
2898 
2899  if (fabs(gp_Vec(BRep_Tool::Pnt(v2), BRep_Tool::Pnt(v3)).Magnitude() - fabs(offset))
2900  <= BRep_Tool::Tolerance(v2) + BRep_Tool::Tolerance(v3)) {
2901  openWire2._Shape.Reverse();
2902  std::swap(v3, v4);
2903  v3.Reverse();
2904  v4.Reverse();
2905  }
2906  else if ((fabs(gp_Vec(BRep_Tool::Pnt(v2), BRep_Tool::Pnt(v4)).Magnitude()
2907  - fabs(offset))
2908  <= BRep_Tool::Tolerance(v2) + BRep_Tool::Tolerance(v4))) {
2909  // orientation is as expected, nothing to do
2910  }
2911  else {
2912  FC_THROWM(
2913  Base::CADKernelError,
2914  "makeOffset2D: fill offset: failed to establish open vertex relationship.");
2915  }
2916 
2917  // now directions of open wires are aligned. Finally. make new wire!
2918  BRepBuilderAPI_MakeWire mkWire;
2919  // add openWire1
2920  BRepTools_WireExplorer it;
2921  for (it.Init(TopoDS::Wire(openWire1.getShape())); it.More(); it.Next()) {
2922  mkWire.Add(it.Current());
2923  }
2924  // add first joining edge
2925  mkWire.Add(BRepBuilderAPI_MakeEdge(v2, v4).Edge());
2926  // add openWire2, in reverse order
2927  openWire2._Shape.Reverse();
2928  for (it.Init(TopoDS::Wire(openWire2.getShape())); it.More(); it.Next()) {
2929  mkWire.Add(it.Current());
2930  }
2931  // add final joining edge
2932  mkWire.Add(BRepBuilderAPI_MakeEdge(v3, v1).Edge());
2933 
2934  mkWire.Build();
2935 
2936  wiresForMakingFaces.push_back(
2937  TopoShape(Tag, Hasher).makeElementShape(mkWire, openWires, op));
2938  }
2939  }
2940 
2941  // make faces
2942  if (wiresForMakingFaces.size() > 0) {
2943  TopoShape face(0, Hasher);
2944  face.makeElementFace(wiresForMakingFaces, nullptr, nullptr, &workingPlane);
2945  expandCompound(face, shapesToReturn);
2946  }
2947  }
2948 
2949  return makeElementCompound(shapesToReturn, op, outputPolicy);
2950 }

3021 TopoShape& TopoShape::makeElementWires(const std::vector<TopoShape>& shapes,
3022  const char* op,
3023  double tol,
3024  ConnectionPolicy policy,
3025  TopoShapeMap* output)
3026 {
3027  if (!op) {
3028  op = Part::OpCodes::Wire;
3029  }
3030  if (tol < Precision::Confusion()) {
3031  tol = Precision::Confusion();
3032  }
3033 
3034  if (policy == ConnectionPolicy::requireSharedVertex) {
3035  // Can't use ShapeAnalysis_FreeBounds if not shared. It seems the output
3036  // edges are modified somehow, and it is not obvious how to map the
3037  // resulting edges.
3038  Handle(TopTools_HSequenceOfShape) hEdges = new TopTools_HSequenceOfShape();
3039  Handle(TopTools_HSequenceOfShape) hWires = new TopTools_HSequenceOfShape();
3040  for (const auto &shape : shapes) {
3041  for (const auto &edge : shape.getSubShapes(TopAbs_EDGE)) {
3042  hEdges->Append(edge);
3043  }
3044  }
3045  if (hEdges->Length() == 0) {
3046  FC_THROWM(NullShapeException, "Null shape");
3047  }
3048  ShapeAnalysis_FreeBounds::ConnectEdgesToWires(hEdges, tol, Standard_True, hWires);
3049  if (hWires->Length() == 0) {
3050  FC_THROWM(NullShapeException, "Null shape");
3051  }
3052 
3053  std::vector<TopoShape> wires;
3054  for (int i = 1; i <= hWires->Length(); i++) {
3055  auto wire = hWires->Value(i);
3056  wires.emplace_back(Tag,Hasher,wire);
3057  wires.back().mapSubElement(shapes, op);
3058  }
3059  return makeElementCompound(wires, "", SingleShapeCompoundCreationPolicy::returnShape);
3060  }
3061 
3062  std::vector<TopoShape> wires;
3063  std::list<TopoShape> edgeList;
3064 
3065  for (const auto &shape : shapes) {
3066  for(const auto &e : shape.getSubTopoShapes(TopAbs_EDGE)) {
3067  edgeList.emplace_back(e);
3068  }
3069  }
3070 
3071  std::vector<TopoShape> edges;
3072  edges.reserve(edgeList.size());
3073  wires.reserve(edgeList.size());
3074 
3075  // sort them together to wires
3076  while (!edgeList.empty()) {
3077  BRepBuilderAPI_MakeWire mkWire;
3078  // add and erase first edge
3079  edges.clear();
3080  edges.push_back(edgeList.front());
3081  mkWire.Add(TopoDS::Edge(edges.back().getShape()));
3082  edges.back().setShape(mkWire.Edge(), false);
3083  if (output) {
3084  (*output)[edges.back()] = edgeList.front();
3085  }
3086  edgeList.pop_front();
3087 
3088  TopoDS_Wire new_wire = mkWire.Wire(); // current new wire
3089 
3090  // try to connect each edge to the wire, the wire is complete if no more edges are
3091  // connectible
3092  bool found = true;
3093  while (found) {
3094  found = false;
3095  for (auto it = edgeList.begin(); it != edgeList.end(); ++it) {
3096  mkWire.Add(TopoDS::Edge(it->getShape()));
3097  if (mkWire.Error() != BRepBuilderAPI_DisconnectedWire) {
3098  // edge added ==> remove it from list
3099  found = true;
3100  edges.push_back(*it);
3101  // MakeWire will replace vertex of connected edge, which
3102  // effectively creat a new edge. So we need to update the
3103  // shape in order to preserve element mapping.
3104  edges.back().setShape(mkWire.Edge(), false);
3105  if (output) {
3106  (*output)[edges.back()] = *it;
3107  }
3108  edgeList.erase(it);
3109  new_wire = mkWire.Wire();
3110  break;
3111  }
3112  }
3113  }
3114 
3115  wires.emplace_back(new_wire);
3116  wires.back().mapSubElement(edges, op);
3117  wires.back().fix();
3118  }
3119  return makeElementCompound(wires, nullptr, SingleShapeCompoundCreationPolicy::returnShape);
3120 }

3126 struct EdgePoints
3127 {
3128  gp_Pnt v1, v2;
3129  std::list<TopoShape>::iterator it;
3130  const TopoShape* edge;
3131  bool closed {false};
3132 
3133  EdgePoints(std::list<TopoShape>::iterator it, double tol)
3134  : it(it)
3135  , edge(&*it)
3136  {

3138  v1 = BRep_Tool::Pnt(TopoDS::Vertex(xp.Current()));
3139  xp.Next();
3140  if (xp.More()) {
3141  v2 = BRep_Tool::Pnt(TopoDS::Vertex(xp.Current()));
3142  closed = (v2.SquareDistance(v1) <= tol);
3143  }
3144  else {
3145  v2 = v1;

3153 TopoShape TopoShape::reverseEdge(const TopoShape& edge)
3154 {
3155  Standard_Real first = NAN;
3156  Standard_Real last = NAN;
3157  const Handle(Geom_Curve)& curve = BRep_Tool::Curve(TopoDS::Edge(edge.getShape()), first, last);
3158  first = curve->ReversedParameter(first);
3159  last = curve->ReversedParameter(last);
3160  TopoShape res(BRepBuilderAPI_MakeEdge(curve->Reversed(), last, first));
3161  auto edgeName = Data::IndexedName::fromConst("Edge", 1);
3162  if (auto mapped = edge.getMappedName(edgeName)) {
3163  res.elementMap()->setElementName(edgeName, mapped, res.Tag);
3164  }
3165  auto v1Name = Data::IndexedName::fromConst("Vertex", 1);
3166  auto v2Name = Data::IndexedName::fromConst("Vertex", 2);
3167  auto v1 = edge.getMappedName(v1Name);
3168  auto v2 = edge.getMappedName(v2Name);
3169  if (v1 && v2) {
3170  res.elementMap()->setElementName(v1Name, v2, res.Tag);
3171  res.elementMap()->setElementName(v2Name, v1, res.Tag);
3172  }
3173  else if (v1 && edge.countSubShapes(TopAbs_EDGE) == 1) {
3174  // It's possible an edge has only one vertex, so no need to reverse
3175  // the name
3176  res.elementMap()->setElementName(v1Name, v1, res.Tag);
3177  }
3178  else if (v1) {
3179  res.elementMap()->setElementName(v2Name, v1, res.Tag);
3180  }
3181  else if (v2) {
3182  res.elementMap()->setElementName(v1Name, v2, res.Tag);
3183  }
3184  return res;
3185 };
