3187 std::deque<TopoShape> TopoShape::sortEdges(std::list<TopoShape>& edges, bool keepOrder, double tol)
3188 {
3189  if (tol < Precision::Confusion()) {
3190  tol = Precision::Confusion();
3191  }
3192  double tol3d = tol * tol;
3193 
3194  std::list<EdgePoints> edgePoints;
3195  for (auto it = edges.begin(); it != edges.end(); ++it) {
3196  edgePoints.emplace_back(it, tol3d);
3197  }
3198 
3199  std::deque<TopoShape> sorted;
3200  if (edgePoints.empty()) {
3201  return sorted;
3202  }
3203 
3204  gp_Pnt first;
3205  gp_Pnt last;
3206  first = edgePoints.front().v1;
3207  last = edgePoints.front().v2;
3208 
3209  sorted.push_back(*edgePoints.front().edge);
3210  edges.erase(edgePoints.front().it);
3211  if (edgePoints.front().closed) {
3212  return sorted;
3213  }
3214 
3215  edgePoints.erase(edgePoints.begin());
3216 
3217  while (!edgePoints.empty()) {
3218  // search for adjacent edge
3219  std::list<EdgePoints>::iterator pEI;
3220  for (pEI = edgePoints.begin(); pEI != edgePoints.end(); ++pEI) {
3221  if (pEI->closed) {
3222  continue;
3223  }
3224 
3225  if (keepOrder && sorted.size() == 1) {
3226  if (pEI->v2.SquareDistance(first) <= tol3d
3227  || pEI->v1.SquareDistance(first) <= tol3d) {
3228  sorted[0] = reverseEdge(sorted[0]);
3229  std::swap(first, last);
3230  }
3231  }
3232 
3233  if (pEI->v1.SquareDistance(last) <= tol3d) {
3234  last = pEI->v2;
3235  sorted.push_back(*pEI->edge);
3236  edges.erase(pEI->it);
3237  edgePoints.erase(pEI);
3238  pEI = edgePoints.begin();
3239  break;
3240  }
3241  if (pEI->v2.SquareDistance(first) <= tol3d) {
3242  sorted.push_front(*pEI->edge);
3243  first = pEI->v1;
3244  edges.erase(pEI->it);
3245  edgePoints.erase(pEI);
3246  pEI = edgePoints.begin();
3247  break;
3248  }
3249  if (pEI->v2.SquareDistance(last) <= tol3d) {
3250  last = pEI->v1;
3251  sorted.push_back(reverseEdge(*pEI->edge));
3252  edges.erase(pEI->it);
3253  edgePoints.erase(pEI);
3254  pEI = edgePoints.begin();
3255  break;
3256  }
3257  if (pEI->v1.SquareDistance(first) <= tol3d) {
3258  first = pEI->v2;
3259  sorted.push_front(reverseEdge(*pEI->edge));
3260  edges.erase(pEI->it);
3261  edgePoints.erase(pEI);
3262  pEI = edgePoints.begin();
3263  break;
3264  }
3265  }
3266 
3267  if ((pEI == edgePoints.end()) || (last.SquareDistance(first) <= tol3d)) {
3268  // no adjacent edge found or polyline is closed
3269  return sorted;
3270  }
3271  }
3272 
3273  return sorted;
3274 }

3276 TopoShape& TopoShape::makeElementOrderedWires(const std::vector<TopoShape>& shapes,
3277  const char* op,
3278  double tol,
3279  TopoShapeMap* output)
3280 {
3281  if (!op) {

3285  tol = Precision::Confusion();

3290 
3291  auto shape =
3292  TopoShape().makeElementCompound(shapes, "", SingleShapeCompoundCreationPolicy::returnShape);
3293  for (auto& edge : shape.getSubTopoShapes(TopAbs_EDGE)) {

3511 struct MapperPrism: MapperMaker
3512 {
3513  std::unordered_map<TopoDS_Shape, TopoDS_Shape, ShapeHasher, ShapeHasher> vertexMap;
3514  ShapeMapper::ShapeMap edgeMap;
3515 
3516  MapperPrism(BRepFeat_MakePrism& maker, const TopoShape& upTo)
3517  : MapperMaker(maker)
3518  {
3519  (void)upTo;
3520 
3521  std::vector<TopoShape> shapes;
3522  for (TopTools_ListIteratorOfListOfShape it(maker.FirstShape()); it.More(); it.Next()) {
3523  shapes.push_back(it.Value());
3524  }
3525 
3526  if (shapes.size()) {
3527  // It seems that BRepFeat_MakePrism::newEdges() does not return
3528  // edges generated by extruding the profile vertices. The following
3529  // code assumes BRepFeat_MakePrism::myFShape is the profile, and
3530  // FirstShape() returns the corresponding faces in the new shape,
3531  // i.e. the bottom profile, and add all edges that shares a
3532  // vertex with the profiles as new edges.
3533 
3534  std::unordered_set<TopoDS_Shape, ShapeHasher, ShapeHasher> edgeSet;
3535  TopoShape bottom;
3536  bottom.makeElementCompound(shapes,
3537  nullptr,
3538  TopoShape::SingleShapeCompoundCreationPolicy::returnShape);
3539  TopoShape shape(maker.Shape());
3540  for (auto& vertex : bottom.getSubShapes(TopAbs_VERTEX)) {
3541  for (auto& e : shape.findAncestorsShapes(vertex, TopAbs_EDGE)) {
3542  // Make sure to not visit the the same edge twice.
3543  // And check only edge that are not found in the bottom profile
3544  if (!edgeSet.insert(e).second && !bottom.findShape(e)) {
3545  auto otherVertex = TopExp::FirstVertex(TopoDS::Edge(e));
3546  if (otherVertex.IsSame(vertex)) {
3547  otherVertex = TopExp::LastVertex(TopoDS::Edge(e));
3548  }
3549  vertexMap[vertex] = otherVertex;
3550  }
3551  }
3552  }
3553 
3554  // Now map each edge in the bottom profile to the extrueded top
3555  // profile. vertexMap created above gives us each pair of vertexes
3556  // of the bottom and top profile. We use it to find the
3557  // corresponding edges in the top profile, what an extra criteria
3558  // for disambiguation. That is, the pair of edges (bottom and top)
3559  // must belong to the same face.
3560  for (auto& edge : bottom.getSubShapes(TopAbs_EDGE)) {
3561  std::vector<int> indices;
3562  auto first = TopExp::FirstVertex(TopoDS::Edge(edge));
3563  auto last = TopExp::LastVertex(TopoDS::Edge(edge));
3564  auto itFirst = vertexMap.find(first);
3565  auto itLast = vertexMap.find(last);
3566  if (itFirst == vertexMap.end() || itLast == vertexMap.end()) {
3567  continue;
3568  }
3569  std::vector<TopoShape> faces;
3570  for (int idx : shape.findAncestors(edge, TopAbs_FACE)) {
3571  faces.push_back(shape.getSubTopoShape(TopAbs_FACE, idx));
3572  }
3573  if (faces.empty()) {
3574  continue;
3575  }
3576  for (int idx : shape.findAncestors(itFirst->second, TopAbs_EDGE)) {
3577  auto e = shape.getSubTopoShape(TopAbs_EDGE, idx);
3578  if (!e.findShape(itLast->second)) {
3579  continue;
3580  }
3581  for (auto& face : faces) {
3582  if (!face.findShape(e.getShape())) {
3583  continue;
3584  }
3585  auto& entry = edgeMap[edge];
3586  if (entry.shapeSet.insert(e.getShape()).second) {
3587  entry.shapes.push_back(e.getShape());
3588  }
3589  }
3590  }
3591  }
3592  }
3593  }
3594  const std::vector<TopoDS_Shape>& generated(const TopoDS_Shape& s) const override
3595  {
3596  _res.clear();
3597  switch (s.ShapeType()) {
3598  case TopAbs_VERTEX: {
3599  auto it = vertexMap.find(s);
3600  if (it != vertexMap.end()) {
3601  _res.push_back(it->second);
3602  return _res;
3603  }
3604  break;
3605  }
3606  case TopAbs_EDGE: {
3607  auto it = edgeMap.find(s);
3608  if (it != edgeMap.end()) {
3609  return it->second.shapes;
3610  }
3611  break;
3612  }
3613  default:
3614  break;
3615  }
3616  MapperMaker::generated(s);
3617  return _res;
3618  }
3619 };

3837  }
3838  }
3839  if (count == 0) {
3840  // no compsolids. Get shells...
3841  BRepBuilderAPI_MakeSolid mkSolid;
3842  count = 0;
3843  for (const auto& s : shape.getSubShapes(TopAbs_SHELL)) {
3844  ++count;
3845  mkSolid.Add(TopoDS::Shell(s));
3846  }
3847 
3848  if (count == 0) { // no shells?
3849  FC_THROWM(Base::CADKernelError, "No shells or compsolids found in shape");
3850  }
3851 
3852  makeElementShape(mkSolid, shape, op);
3853 
3854  TopoDS_Solid solid = TopoDS::Solid(_Shape);
3855  BRepLib::OrientClosedSolid(solid);
3856  setShape(solid, false);
3857  }
3858  else if (count == 1) {
3859  BRepBuilderAPI_MakeSolid mkSolid(compsolid);
3860  makeElementShape(mkSolid, shape, op);
3861  }
3862  else { // if (count > 1)
3863  FC_THROWM(Base::CADKernelError,
3864  "Only one compsolid can be accepted. "
3865  "Provided shape has more than one compsolid.");
3866  }
3867  return *this;
3868 }

3990 TopoShape& TopoShape::makeElementChamfer(const TopoShape& shape,
3991  const std::vector<TopoShape>& edges,
3992  ChamferType chamferType,
3993  double radius1,
3994  double radius2,
3995  const char* op,
3996  Flip flipDirection)
3997 {
3998  if (!op) {
3999  op = Part::OpCodes::Chamfer;
4000  }
4001  if (shape.isNull()) {
4002  FC_THROWM(NullShapeException, "Null shape");
4003  }
4004  if (edges.empty()) {
4005  FC_THROWM(NullShapeException, "Null input shape");
4006  }
4007  BRepFilletAPI_MakeChamfer mkChamfer(shape.getShape());
4008  for (auto& e : edges) {
4009  const auto& edge = e.getShape();
4010  if (e.isNull()) {
4011  FC_THROWM(NullShapeException, "Null input shape");
4012  }
4013  if (!shape.findShape(edge)) {
4014  FC_THROWM(Base::CADKernelError, "edge does not belong to the shape");

4016  // Add edge to fillet algorithm
4017  TopoDS_Shape face;
4018  if (flipDirection == Flip::flip) {
4019  face = shape.findAncestorsShapes(edge, TopAbs_FACE).back();
4020  }
4021  else {

4024  switch (chamferType) {

4028  case ChamferType::twoDistances: // Two distances
4029  mkChamfer.Add(radius1, radius2, TopoDS::Edge(edge), TopoDS::Face(face));
4030  break;
4031  case ChamferType::distanceAngle: // Distance and angle
4032  mkChamfer.AddDA(radius1,
4033  Base::toRadians(radius2),
4034  TopoDS::Edge(edge),
4035  TopoDS::Face(face));

4143 TopoShape& TopoShape::makeElementLoft(const std::vector<TopoShape>& shapes,
4144  IsSolid isSolid,
4145  IsRuled isRuled,
4146  IsClosed isClosed,
4147  Standard_Integer maxDegree,
4148  const char* op)
4149 {
4150  if (!op) {
4151  op = Part::OpCodes::Loft;
4152  }
4153 
4154  // http://opencascade.blogspot.com/2010/01/surface-modeling-part5.html
4155  BRepOffsetAPI_ThruSections aGenerator(isSolid == IsSolid::solid, isRuled == IsRuled::ruled);
4156  aGenerator.SetMaxDegree(maxDegree);
4157 
4158  auto profiles = prepareProfiles(shapes);
4159  if (shapes.size() < 2) {
4160  FC_THROWM(Base::CADKernelError,
4161  "Need at least two vertices, edges or wires to create loft face");
4162  }
4163 
4164  int i=0;
4165  Base::Vector3d center1,center2;
4166  for (auto& sh : profiles) {
4167  if (i>0) {
4168  if (sh.getCenterOfGravity(center1) && profiles[i-1].getCenterOfGravity(center2) && center1.IsEqual(center2,Precision::Confusion())) {
4169  FC_THROWM(Base::CADKernelError,
4170  "Segments of a Loft/Pad do not have sufficient separation");
4171  }
4172  }
4173  const auto& shape = sh.getShape();
4174  if (shape.ShapeType() == TopAbs_VERTEX) {
4175  aGenerator.AddVertex(TopoDS::Vertex(shape));
4176  }
4177  else {
4178  aGenerator.AddWire(TopoDS::Wire(shape));
4179  }
4180  i++;
4181  }
4182  // close loft by duplicating initial profile as last profile. not perfect.
4183  if (isClosed == IsClosed::closed) {
4184  /* can only close loft in certain combinations of Vertex/Wire(Edge):
4185  - V1-W1-W2-W3-V2 ==> V1-W1-W2-W3-V2-V1 invalid closed
4186  - V1-W1-W2-W3 ==> V1-W1-W2-W3-V1 valid closed
4187  - W1-W2-W3-V1 ==> W1-W2-W3-V1-W1 invalid closed
4188  - W1-W2-W3 ==> W1-W2-W3-W1 valid closed*/
4189  if (profiles.back().getShape().ShapeType() == TopAbs_VERTEX) {
4190  Base::Console().Message("TopoShape::makeLoft: can't close Loft with Vertex as last "
4191  "profile. 'Closed' ignored.\n");
4192  }
4193  else {
4194  // repeat Add logic above for first profile
4195  const TopoDS_Shape& firstProfile = profiles.front().getShape();
4196  if (firstProfile.ShapeType() == TopAbs_VERTEX) {
4197  aGenerator.AddVertex(TopoDS::Vertex(firstProfile));
4198  }
4199  else if (firstProfile.ShapeType() == TopAbs_EDGE) {
4200  aGenerator.AddWire(BRepBuilderAPI_MakeWire(TopoDS::Edge(firstProfile)).Wire());
4201  }
4202  else if (firstProfile.ShapeType() == TopAbs_WIRE) {
4203  aGenerator.AddWire(TopoDS::Wire(firstProfile));
4204  }
4205  }
4206  }
4207 
4208  Standard_Boolean anIsCheck = Standard_True;
4209  aGenerator.CheckCompatibility(anIsCheck); // use BRepFill_CompatibleWires on profiles. force
4210  // #edges, orientation, "origin" to match.
4211 
4212  aGenerator.Build();
4213  return makeShapeWithElementMap(aGenerator.Shape(),
4214  MapperThruSections(aGenerator, profiles),
4215  shapes,
4216  op);
4217 }

4230 
4231 TopoShape& TopoShape::makeElementPrismUntil(const TopoShape& _base,
4232  const TopoShape& profile,
4233  const TopoShape& supportFace,
4234  const TopoShape& __uptoface,
4235  const gp_Dir& direction,
4236  PrismMode Mode,
4237  Standard_Boolean checkLimits,
4238  const char* op)
4239 {
4240  if (!op) {
4241  op = Part::OpCodes::Prism;
4242  }
4243 
4244  BRepFeat_MakePrism PrismMaker;
4245 
4246  // don't remove limits of concave face
4247  if (checkLimits && __uptoface.shapeType(true) == TopAbs_FACE){
4248  Base::Vector3d vCog;
4249  profile.getCenterOfGravity(vCog);
4250  gp_Pnt pCog(vCog.x, vCog.y, vCog.z);
4251  checkLimits = ! Part::Tools::isConcave(TopoDS::Face(__uptoface.getShape()), pCog , direction);
4252  }
4253 
4254  TopoShape _uptoface(__uptoface);
4255  if (checkLimits && _uptoface.shapeType(true) == TopAbs_FACE
4256  && !BRep_Tool::NaturalRestriction(TopoDS::Face(_uptoface.getShape()))) {
4257  // When using the face with BRepFeat_MakePrism::Perform(const TopoDS_Shape& Until)
4258  // then the algorithm expects that the 'NaturalRestriction' flag is set in order
4259  // to work as expected.
4260  BRep_Builder builder;
4261  _uptoface = _uptoface.makeElementCopy();
4262  builder.NaturalRestriction(TopoDS::Face(_uptoface.getShape()), Standard_True);
4263  }
4264 
4265  TopoShape uptoface(_uptoface);
4266  TopoShape base(_base);
4267 
4268  if (base.isNull()) {
4269  Mode = PrismMode::None;
4270  base = profile;
4271  }
4272 
4273  // Check whether the face has limits or not. Unlimited faces have no wire
4274  // Note: Datum planes are always unlimited
4275  if (checkLimits && uptoface.shapeType(true) == TopAbs_FACE
4276  && uptoface.hasSubShape(TopAbs_WIRE)) {
4277  TopoDS_Face face = TopoDS::Face(uptoface.getShape());
4278  bool remove_limits = false;
4279  // Remove the limits of the upToFace so that the extrusion works even if profile is larger
4280  // than the upToFace
4281  for (auto& sketchface : profile.getSubTopoShapes(TopAbs_FACE)) {
4282  // Get outermost wire of sketch face
4283  TopoShape outerWire = sketchface.splitWires();
4284  BRepProj_Projection proj(TopoDS::Wire(outerWire.getShape()), face, direction);
4285  if (!proj.More() || !proj.Current().Closed()) {
4286  remove_limits = true;
4287  break;
4288  }
4289  }
4290 
4291  // It must also be checked that all projected inner wires of the upToFace
4292  // lie outside the sketch shape. If this is not the case then the sketch
4293  // shape is not completely covered by the upToFace. See #0003141
4294  if (!remove_limits) {
4295  std::vector<TopoShape> wires;
4296  uptoface.splitWires(&wires);
4297  for (auto& w : wires) {
4298  BRepProj_Projection proj(TopoDS::Wire(w.getShape()),
4299  profile.getShape(),
4300  -direction);
4301  if (proj.More()) {
4302  remove_limits = true;
4303  break;
4304  }
4305  }
4306  }
4307 
4308  if (remove_limits) {
4309  // Note: Using an unlimited face every time gives unnecessary failures for concave
4310  // faces
4311  TopLoc_Location loc = face.Location();
4312  BRepAdaptor_Surface adapt(face, Standard_False);
4313  // use the placement of the adapter, not of the upToFace
4314  loc = TopLoc_Location(adapt.Trsf());
4315  BRepBuilderAPI_MakeFace mkFace(adapt.Surface().Surface(), Precision::Confusion());
4316  if (mkFace.IsDone()) {
4317  uptoface.setShape(located(mkFace.Shape(), loc), false);
4318  }
4319  }
4320  }
4321 
4322  TopoShape uptofaceCopy = uptoface;
4323  bool checkBase = false;
4324  auto retry = [&]() {
4325  if (!uptoface.isSame(_uptoface)) {
4326  // retry using the original up to face in case unnecessary failure
4327  // due to removing the limits
4328  uptoface = _uptoface;
4329  return true;
4330  }
4331  if ((!_base.isNull() && base.isSame(_base)) || (_base.isNull() && base.isSame(profile))) {
4332  // It is unclear under exactly what condition extrude up to face
4333  // can fail. Either the support face or the up to face must be part
4334  // of the base, or maybe some thing else.
4335  //
4336  // To deal with it, we retry again by disregard the supplied base,
4337  // and use up to face to extrude our own base. Later on, use the
4338  // supplied base (i.e. _base) to calculate the final shape if the
4339  // mode is FuseWithBase or CutWithBase.
4340  checkBase = true;
4341  uptoface = uptofaceCopy;
4342  base.makeElementPrism(_uptoface, direction);
4343  return true;
4344  }
4345  return false;
4346  };
4347 
4348  std::vector<TopoShape> srcShapes;
4349  TopoShape result;
4350  for (;;) {
4351  try {
4352  result = base;
4353 
4354  // We do not rely on BRepFeat_MakePrism to perform fuse or cut for
4355  // us because of its poor support of shape history.
4356  auto mode = PrismMode::None;
4357 
4358  for (auto& face : profile.getSubTopoShapes(
4359  profile.hasSubShape(TopAbs_FACE) ? TopAbs_FACE : TopAbs_WIRE)) {
4360  srcShapes.clear();
4361  if (!profile.isNull() && !result.findShape(profile.getShape())) {
4362  srcShapes.push_back(profile);
4363  }
4364  if (!supportFace.isNull() && !result.findShape(supportFace.getShape())) {
4365  srcShapes.push_back(supportFace);
4366  }
4367 
4368  // DO NOT include uptoface for element mapping. Because OCCT
4369  // BRepFeat_MakePrism will report all top extruded face being
4370  // modified by the uptoface. If there are more than one face in
4371  // the profile, this will cause unnecessary duplicated element
4372  // mapped name. And will also disrupte element history tracing
4373  // back to the profile sketch.
4374  //
4375  // if (!uptoface.isNull() && !this->findShape(uptoface.getShape()))
4376  // srcShapes.push_back(uptoface);
4377 
4378  srcShapes.push_back(result);
4379 
4380  if (result.isInfinite()){
4381  result = face;
4382  }
4383 
4384  PrismMaker.Init(result.getShape(),
4385  face.getShape(),
4386  TopoDS::Face(supportFace.getShape()),
4387  direction,
4388  mode,
4389  Standard_False);
4390  mode = PrismMode::FuseWithBase;
4391 
4392  PrismMaker.Perform(uptoface.getShape());
4393 
4394  if (!PrismMaker.IsDone() || PrismMaker.Shape().IsNull()) {
4395  FC_THROWM(Base::CADKernelError, "BRepFeat_MakePrism: extrusion failed");
4396  }
4397 
4398  result.makeElementShape(PrismMaker, srcShapes, uptoface, op);
4399  }
4400  break;
4401  }
4402  catch (Base::Exception&) {
4403  if (!retry()) {
4404  throw;
4405  }
4406  }
4407  catch (Standard_Failure&) {
4408  if (!retry()) {
4409  throw;
4410  }
4411  }
4412  }
4413 
4414  if (!_base.isNull() && Mode != PrismMode::None) {
4415  if (Mode == PrismMode::FuseWithBase) {
4416  result.makeElementFuse({_base, result});
4417  }
4418  else {
4419  result.makeElementCut({_base, result});
4420  }
4421  }
4422 
4423  *this = result;
4424  return *this;
4425 }

4427 TopoShape& TopoShape::makeElementRevolve(const TopoShape& _base,
4428  const gp_Ax1& axis,
4429  double d,
4430  const char* face_maker,
4431  const char* op)
4432 {
4433  if (!op) {
4434  op = Part::OpCodes::Revolve;
4435  }
4436 
4437  TopoShape base(_base);
4438  if (base.isNull()) {
4439  FC_THROWM(NullShapeException, "Null shape");

4725  last = bspline->LastParameter();

4729  auto m2 = m1 + step;

4732  auto c2 = GeomConvert::SplitBSplineCurve(bspline, m1, m2, Precision::Confusion());
4733  auto c3 = GeomConvert::SplitBSplineCurve(bspline, m2, m3, Precision::Confusion());

4736  mk2.Init(c2);
4737  mk3.Init(c3);

4769  }

4772  switch (style) {
4773  case coons:

4777  fstyle = GeomFill_CurvedStyle;

4794  if (!curve) {

4993 std::vector<Data::MappedName> TopoShape::decodeElementComboName(const Data::IndexedName& element,
4994  const Data::MappedName& name,
4995  const char* marker,
4996  std::string* postfix) const
4997 {
4998  std::vector<Data::MappedName> names;
4999  if (!element) {
5000  return names;
5001  }
5002  if (!marker) {
5003  marker = "";
5004  }
5005  int plen = (int)elementMapPrefix().size();
5006  int markerLen = strlen(marker);
5007  int len;
5008  int pos = name.findTagInElementName(nullptr, &len);
5009  if (pos < 0) {
5010  // It is possible to encode combo name without using a tag, e.g.
5011  // Sketcher object creates wire using edges that are created by itself,
5012  // so there will be no tag to encode.
5013  //
5014  // In this case, just search for the brackets
5015  len = name.find("(");
5016  if (len < 0) {
5017  // No bracket is also possible, if there is only one name in the combo
5018  pos = len = name.size();
5019  }
5020  else {
5021  pos = name.find(")");
5022  if (pos < 0) {
5023  // non closing bracket?
5024  return {};
5025  }
5026  ++pos;
5027  }
5028  if (len <= (int)markerLen) {
5029  return {};
5030  }
5031  len -= markerLen + plen;
5032  }
5033 
5034  if (name.find(elementMapPrefix(), len) != len || name.find(marker, len + plen) != len + plen) {
5035  return {};
5036  }
5037 
5038  names.emplace_back(name, 0, len);
5039 
5040  std::string text;
5041  len += plen + markerLen;
5042  name.appendToBuffer(text, len, pos - len);
5043 
5044  if (this->Hasher) {
5045  if (auto id = App::StringID::fromString(names.back().toRawBytes())) {
5046  if (App::StringIDRef sid = this->Hasher->getID(id)) {
5047  names.pop_back();
5048  names.emplace_back(sid);
5049  }
5050  else {
5051  return names;
5052  }
5053  }
5054  if (auto id = App::StringID::fromString(text.c_str())) {
5055  if (App::StringIDRef sid = this->Hasher->getID(id)) {
5056  text = sid.dataToText();
5057  }
5058  else {
5059  return names;
5060  }
5061  }
5062  }
5063  if (text.empty() || text[0] != '(') {
5064  return names;
5065  }
5066  auto endPos = text.rfind(')');
5067  if (endPos == std::string::npos) {
5068  return names;
5069  }
5070 
5071  if (postfix) {
5072  *postfix = text.substr(endPos + 1);
5073  }
5074 
5075  text.resize(endPos);
5076  std::istringstream iss(text.c_str() + 1);
5077  std::string token;
5078  while (std::getline(iss, token, '|')) {
5079  names.emplace_back(token);
5080  }
5081  return names;
5082 }
5083 
5094 TopoShape TopoShape::splitWires(std::vector<TopoShape>* inner, SplitWireReorient reorient) const
5095 {
5096  // ShapeAnalysis::OuterWire() is un-reliable for some reason. OCC source
5097  // code shows it works by creating face using each wire, and then test using
5098  // BRepTopAdaptor_FClass2d::PerformInfinitePoint() to check if it is an
5099  // outbound wire. And practice shows it sometimes returns the incorrect
5100  // result. Need more investigation. Note that this may be related to
5101  // unreliable solid face orientation
5102  // (https://forum.freecadweb.org/viewtopic.php?p=446006#p445674)
5103  //
5104  // Use BrepTools::OuterWire() instead. OCC source code shows it is
5105  // implemented using simple bound box checking. This should be a
5106  // reliable method, especially so for a planar face.
5107 
5108  TopoDS_Shape tmp;
5109  if (shapeType(true) == TopAbs_FACE) {
5110  tmp = BRepTools::OuterWire(TopoDS::Face(_Shape));
5111  }
5112  else if (countSubShapes(TopAbs_FACE) == 1) {
5113  tmp = BRepTools::OuterWire(TopoDS::Face(getSubShape(TopAbs_FACE, 1)));
5114  }
5115  if (tmp.IsNull()) {
5116  return TopoShape {};
5117  }
5118  const auto& wires = getSubTopoShapes(TopAbs_WIRE);
5119  auto it = wires.begin();
5120 
5121  TopAbs_Orientation orientOuter, orientInner;
5122  switch (reorient) {
5123  case ReorientReversed:
5124  orientOuter = orientInner = TopAbs_REVERSED;
5125  break;
5126  case ReorientForward:
5127  orientOuter = orientInner = TopAbs_FORWARD;
5128  break;
5129  default:
5130  orientOuter = TopAbs_FORWARD;
5131  orientInner = TopAbs_REVERSED;
5132  break;
5133  }
5134 
5135  auto doReorient = [](TopoShape& s, TopAbs_Orientation orient) {
5136  // Special case of single edge wire. Make sure the edge is in the
5137  // required orientation. This is necessary because BRepFill_OffsetWire
5138  // has special handling of circular edge offset, which seem to only
5139  // respect the edge orientation and disregard the wire orientation. The
5140  // orientation is used to determine whether to shrink or expand.
5141  if (s.countSubShapes(TopAbs_EDGE) == 1) {
5142  TopoDS_Shape e = s.getSubShape(TopAbs_EDGE, 1);
5143  if (e.Orientation() == orient) {
5144  if (s._Shape.Orientation() == orient) {
5145  return;
5146  }
5147  }
5148  else {
5149  e = e.Oriented(orient);
5150  }
5151  BRepBuilderAPI_MakeWire mkWire(TopoDS::Edge(e));
5152  s.setShape(mkWire.Shape(), false);
5153  }
5154  else if (s._Shape.Orientation() != orient) {
5155  s.setShape(s._Shape.Oriented(orient), false);
5156  }
5157  };
5158 
5159  for (; it != wires.end(); ++it) {
5160  auto& wire = *it;
5161  if (wire.getShape().IsSame(tmp)) {
5162  if (inner) {
5163  for (++it; it != wires.end(); ++it) {
5164  inner->push_back(*it);
5165  if (reorient) {
5166  doReorient(inner->back(), orientInner);
5167  }
5168  }
5169  }
5170  auto res = wire;
5171  if (reorient) {
5172  doReorient(res, orientOuter);
5173  }
5174  return res;
5175  }
5176  if (inner) {
5177  inner->push_back(wire);
5178  if (reorient) {
5179  doReorient(inner->back(), orientInner);
5180  }
5181  }
5182  }
5183  return TopoShape {};
5184 }

5214 // TODO: Refactor this into two methods. Totally separate concerns here.
5215 bool TopoShape::linearize(LinearizeFace do_face, LinearizeEdge do_edge)
5216 {
5217  bool touched = false;
5218  BRep_Builder builder;
5219  // Note: changing edge geometry seems to mess up with face (or shell, or solid)
5220  // Probably need to do some fix afterwards.
5221  if (do_edge == LinearizeEdge::linearizeEdges) {
5222  for (auto& edge : getSubTopoShapes(TopAbs_EDGE)) {
5223  TopoDS_Edge e = TopoDS::Edge(edge.getShape());
5224  BRepAdaptor_Curve curve(e);
5225  if (curve.GetType() == GeomAbs_Line || !edge.isLinearEdge()) {
5226  continue;
5227  }
5228  std::unique_ptr<Geometry> geo(
5229  Geometry::fromShape(e.Located(TopLoc_Location()).Oriented(TopAbs_FORWARD)));
5230  std::unique_ptr<Geometry> gline(static_cast<GeomCurve*>(geo.get())->toLine());
5231  if (gline) {
5232  touched = true;
5233  builder.UpdateEdge(e,
5234  Handle(Geom_Curve)::DownCast(gline->handle()),
5235  e.Location(),
5236  BRep_Tool::Tolerance(e));
5237  }
5238  }
5239  }
5240  if (do_face == LinearizeFace::linearizeFaces) {
5241  for (auto& face : getSubTopoShapes(TopAbs_FACE)) {
5242  TopoDS_Face f = TopoDS::Face(face.getShape());
5243  BRepAdaptor_Surface surf(f);
5244  if (surf.GetType() == GeomAbs_Plane || !face.isPlanarFace()) {
5245  continue;
5246  }
5247  std::unique_ptr<Geometry> geo(
5248  Geometry::fromShape(f.Located(TopLoc_Location()).Oriented(TopAbs_FORWARD)));
5249  std::unique_ptr<Geometry> gplane(static_cast<GeomSurface*>(geo.get())->toPlane());
5250  if (gplane) {
5251  touched = true;
5252  builder.UpdateFace(f,
5253  Handle(Geom_Surface)::DownCast(gplane->handle()),
5254  f.Location(),
5255  BRep_Tool::Tolerance(f));
5256  }
5257  }
5258  }
5259  return touched;
5260 }

5376 // topo naming counterpart of TopoShape::makeShell()
5377 TopoShape& TopoShape::makeElementShell(bool silent, const char* op)
5378 {
5379  if (silent) {
5380  if (isNull()) {
5381  return *this;
5382  }
5383 
5384  if (shapeType(true) != TopAbs_COMPOUND) {
5385  return *this;
5386  }
5387 
5388  // we need a compound that consists of only faces
5389  TopExp_Explorer it;
5390  // no shells
5391  if (hasSubShape(TopAbs_SHELL)) {
5392  return *this;
5393  }
5394 
5395  // no wires outside a face
5396  it.Init(_Shape, TopAbs_WIRE, TopAbs_FACE);
5397  if (it.More()) {
5398  return *this;
5399  }
5400 
5401  // no edges outside a wire
5402  it.Init(_Shape, TopAbs_EDGE, TopAbs_WIRE);
5403  if (it.More()) {
5404  return *this;
5405  }
5406 
5407  // no vertexes outside an edge
5408  it.Init(_Shape, TopAbs_VERTEX, TopAbs_EDGE);
5409  if (it.More()) {
5410  return *this;
5411  }
5412  }
5413  else if (!hasSubShape(TopAbs_FACE)) {
5414  FC_THROWM(Base::CADKernelError, "Cannot make shell without face");
5415  }
5416 
5417  BRep_Builder builder;
5418  TopoDS_Shape shape;
5419  TopoDS_Shell shell;
5420  builder.MakeShell(shell);
5421 
5422  try {
5423  for (const auto& face : getSubShapes(TopAbs_FACE)) {
5424  builder.Add(shell, face);
5425  }
5426 
5427  TopoShape tmp(Tag, Hasher, shell);
5428  tmp.resetElementMap();
5429  tmp.mapSubElement(*this, op);
5430 
5431  shape = shell;
5432  BRepCheck_Analyzer check(shell);
5433  if (!check.IsValid()) {
5434  ShapeUpgrade_ShellSewing sewShell;
5435  shape = sewShell.ApplySewing(shell);
5436  // TODO confirm the above won't change OCCT topological naming
5437  }
5438 
5439  if (shape.IsNull()) {
5440  if (silent) {
5441  return *this;
5442  }
5443  FC_THROWM(NullShapeException, "Failed to make shell");
5444  }
5445 
5446  if (shape.ShapeType() != TopAbs_SHELL) {
5447  if (silent) {
5448  return *this;
5449  }

5451  "Failed to make shell: unexpected output shape type "
5452  << shapeType(shape.ShapeType(), true));
5453  }
5454 
5455  setShape(shape);
5456  resetElementMap(tmp.elementMap());
5457  }
5458  catch (Standard_Failure& e) {
5459  if (!silent) {
5460  FC_THROWM(Base::CADKernelError, "Failed to make shell: " << e.GetMessageString());

5615  BRep_Builder builder;
5616  TopoDS_Shell shell;
5617  builder.MakeShell(shell);
5618  for (auto& s : shapes) {
5619  builder.Add(shell, s.getShape());
5620  }

5624  if (!check.IsValid()) {
5625  ShapeUpgrade_ShellSewing sewShell;
5626  setShape(sewShell.ApplySewing(shell), false);
5627  // TODO: confirm the above won't change OCCT topological naming

5630  }

5633

5635  if (strcmp(maker, Part::OpCodes::Fuse) == 0) {

5638  if (s.isNull()) {

5647  }
5648  expandCompound(s, _shapes);
5649  }
5650  else if (_shapes.size()) {
5651  _shapes.push_back(s);
5652  }
5653  }
5654  }
5655  else if (strcmp(maker, Part::OpCodes::Cut) == 0) {

5663  _shapes.insert(_shapes.end(), shapes.begin(), shapes.begin() + i);
5664  }
5665  expandCompound(s, _shapes);
5666  }
5667  else if (_shapes.size()) {

5731  // 01/22/2024 This will be an extremely rare case, since we don't

5733  mk->SetRunParallel(true);
5734 #endif
5735 
5736  mk->SetArguments(shapeArguments);
5737  mk->SetTools(shapeTools);
5738  if (tolerance > 0.0) {
5739  mk->SetFuzzyValue(tolerance);
5740  } else if (tolerance < 0.0) {
5741  FCBRepAlgoAPIHelper::setAutoFuzzy(mk.get());
5742  }
5743  mk->Build();
5744  makeElementShape(*mk, inputs, op);
5745

5755  return false;
5756  }

5762 long TopoShape::isElementGenerated(const Data::MappedName& _name, int depth) const
5763 {
5764  long res = 0;
5765  long tag = 0;
5766  traceElement(_name, [&](const Data::MappedName& name, int offset, long tag2, long) {
5767  (void)offset;
5768  if (tag2 < 0) {
5769  tag2 = -tag2;
5770  }
5771  if (tag && tag2 != tag) {
5772  if (--depth < 1) {
5773  return true;
5774  }
5775  }
5776  tag = tag2;
5777  if (depth == 1 && name.startsWith(genPostfix(), offset)) {
5778  res = tag;
5779  return true;
5780  }
5781  return false;
5782  });
5783 
5784  return res;
5785 }

5828 Data::MappedElement TopoShape::chooseMatchingSubShapeByPlaneOrLine(const TopoShape& shapeToFind, const TopoShape& shapeToLookIn)
5829 {
5830  Data::MappedElement result;
5831  // See if we have a Face. If so, try to match using a plane.
5832  auto targetShape = shapeToFind.getSubTopoShape("Face", true);
5833  if ( ! targetShape.isNull() ) {
5834  int index = 0;
5835  for ( const auto& searchFace : shapeToLookIn.getSubTopoShapes(TopAbs_FACE)) {
5836  index++; // We have to generate the element index.
5837  if ( targetShape.isCoplanar(searchFace) ) {
5838  if ( ! result.name.empty() )
5839  return {}; // Found more than one, invalidate our guess. Future: return all matches to the UI?
5840  result = shapeToLookIn.getElementName(("Face"+std::to_string(index)).c_str());
5841  }
5842  }
5843  }
5844  // Alternatively, try to locate an Edge, and try to match. Currently by exact equivalence; later can improve.
5845  targetShape = shapeToFind.getSubTopoShape("Edge", true);
5846  if ( ! targetShape.isNull() ) { // Try to match edges
5847  int index = 0;
5848  for ( const auto& searchEdge : shapeToLookIn.getSubTopoShapes(TopAbs_EDGE)) {
5849  index++;
5850  if ( targetShape.isSame(searchEdge) ) { // TODO: Test for edges that are collinear as really what we want
5851  if ( ! result.name.empty() )
5852  return {}; // Found more than one
5853  result = shapeToLookIn.getElementName(("Edge"+std::to_string(index)).c_str());
5854  }
5855  }
5856  }
5857  return result;
5858 }
